# Book: Proverbs

# Section: The proverbs of Solomon
# Proverbs 01:01
The proverbs of Solomon,
the son of David,
king of Israel.

# Section: To know wisdom and instruction
# Proverbs 01:02
To know wisdom and instruction;
to discern the words of understanding;
# Proverbs 01:03
to receive instruction in wise dealing,
  in righteousness,
  justice,
  and equity;
# Proverbs 01:04
to give prudence to the simple,
knowledge and discretion to the young man ---
# Proverbs 01:05
that the wise man may hear,
and increase in learning;
that the man of understanding may attain to sound counsel;
# Proverbs 01:06
to understand a proverb and parables,
the words and riddles of the wise.

# Section: The fear of Yahweh is the beginning of knowledge
# Proverbs 01:07
The fear of Yahweh is the beginning of knowledge,
but the foolish despise wisdom and instruction.

# Section: My son
# Proverbs 01:08
My son,
listen to your father's instruction,
and don't forsake your mother's teaching;
# Proverbs 01:09
for they will be a garland to grace your head,
and chains around your neck.

# Section: My son
# Proverbs 01:10
My son,
if sinners entice you,
don't consent.

# Proverbs 01:11
If they say,
{
  Come with us.

  Let's lie in wait for blood.

  Let's lurk secretly for the innocent without cause.

  # Proverbs 01:12
  Let's swallow them up alive like Sheol,
  and whole,
  like those who go down into the pit.

  # Proverbs 01:13
  We’ll find all valuable wealth.

  We’ll fill our houses with plunder.

  # Proverbs 01:14
  You shall cast your lot among us.

  We’ll all have one purse.
}

# Section: My son
# Proverbs 01:15
My son,
don't walk on the path with them.

Keep your foot from their path,
# Proverbs 01:16
for their feet run to evil.

They hurry to shed blood.

# Proverbs 01:17
For the net is spread in vain in the sight of any bird;
# Proverbs 01:18
but these lay in wait for their own blood.

They lurk secretly for their own lives.

# Proverbs 01:19
So are the ways of everyone who is greedy for gain.

It takes away the life of its owners.

# Section: Wisdom calls aloud in the street.
# Proverbs 01:20
Wisdom calls aloud in the street.

She utters her voice in the public squares.

# Proverbs 01:21
She calls at the head of noisy places.

At the entrance of the city gates,
she utters her words:

# Proverbs 01:22
{
  How long, you simple ones,
  will you love simplicity?

  How long will mockers delight themselves in mockery,
  and fools hate knowledge?

  # Proverbs 01:23
  Turn at my reproof.

  Behold! I will pour out my spirit on you.

  I will make known my words to you.
}

# Section:   Because I have called
{
  # Proverbs 01:24
  Because I have called,
  and you have refused;
  I have stretched out my hand,
  and no one has paid attention;
  # Proverbs 01:25
  but you have ignored all my counsel,
  and wanted none of my reproof;
  # Proverbs 01:26
  I also will laugh at your disaster.

  I will mock when calamity overtakes you,
  # Proverbs 01:27
  when calamity overtakes you like a storm,
  when your disaster comes on like a whirlwind,
  when distress and anguish come on you.

  # Proverbs 01:28
  Then they will call on me,
  but I will not answer.

  They will seek me diligently,
  but they will not find me,
  # Proverbs 01:29
  because they hated knowledge,
  and didn’t choose the fear of Yahweh.

  # Proverbs 01:30
  They wanted none of my counsel.

  They despised all my reproof.

  # Proverbs 01:31
  Therefore they will eat of the fruit of their own way,
  and be filled with their own schemes.

  # Proverbs 01:32
  For the backsliding of the simple will kill them.

  The careless ease of fools will destroy them.

  # Proverbs 01:33
  But whoever listens to me will dwell securely,
  and will be at ease,
  without fear of harm.
}

# Section: My son
# Proverbs 02:01
My son,
if you will receive my words,
and store up my commandments within you,
# Proverbs 02:02
so as to turn your ear to wisdom,
and apply your heart to understanding;
# Proverbs 02:03
yes, if you call out for discernment,
and lift up your voice for understanding;
# Proverbs 02:04
if you seek her as silver,
and search for her as for hidden treasures;
# Proverbs 02:05
then you will understand the fear of Yahweh,
and find the knowledge of God.

# Section: For Yahweh gives wisdom.
# Proverbs 02:06
For Yahweh gives wisdom.

Out of his mouth comes knowledge and understanding.

# Proverbs 02:07
He lays up sound wisdom for the upright.

# Section: He is a shield
He is a shield to those who walk in integrity,
# Proverbs 02:08
that he may guard the paths of justice,
and preserve the way of his saints.

# Proverbs 02:09
Then you will understand righteousness and justice,
equity and every good path.

# Section: For wisdom will enter into your heart.
# Proverbs 02:10
For wisdom will enter into your heart.

Knowledge will be pleasant to your soul.

# Proverbs 02:11
Discretion will watch over you.

Understanding will keep you,
# Proverbs 02:12
to deliver you from the way of evil,
from the men who speak perverse things,
# Proverbs 02:13
who forsake the paths of uprightness,
to walk in the ways of darkness,
# Proverbs 02:14
who rejoice to do evil,
and delight in the perverseness of evil,
# Proverbs 02:15
who are crooked in their ways,
and wayward in their paths,
# Proverbs 02:16
to deliver you from the strange woman,
even from the foreigner who flatters with her words,
# Proverbs 02:17
who forsakes the friend of her youth,
and forgets the covenant of her God;
# Proverbs 02:18
for her house leads down to death,
her paths to the departed spirits.

# Proverbs 02:19
None who go to her return again,
neither do they attain to the paths of life.

# Section: Therefore walk in the way of good men
# Proverbs 02:20
Therefore walk in the way of good men,
and keep the paths of the righteous.

# Proverbs 02:21
For the upright will dwell in the land.

The perfect will remain in it.

# Proverbs 02:22
But the wicked will be cut off from the land.

The treacherous will be rooted out of it.

# Section: My son
# Proverbs 03:01
My son,
don't forget my teaching,
but let your heart keep my commandments,
# Proverbs 03:02
for they will add to you
  length of days,
  years of life,
  and peace.

# Proverbs 03:03
Don't let kindness and truth forsake you.

  Bind them around your neck.

  Write them on the tablet of your heart.

# Proverbs 03:04
So you will find favor and good understanding
in the sight of God and man.

# Section: Trust in Yahweh with all your heart
# Proverbs 03:05
Trust in Yahweh with all your heart,
and don't lean on your own understanding.

# Proverbs 03:06
In all your ways acknowledge him,
and he will make your paths straight.

# Proverbs 03:07
Don't be wise in your own eyes.

# Section: Fear Yahweh
Fear Yahweh,
and depart from evil.

# Proverbs 03:08
It will be health to your body,
and nourishment to your bones.

# Section: Honor Yahweh with your substance
# Proverbs 03:09
Honor Yahweh with your substance,
with the first fruits of all your increase;
# Proverbs 03:10
so your barns will be filled with plenty,
and your vats will overflow with new wine.

# Section: My son
# Proverbs 03:11
My son,
don't despise Yahweh's discipline,
neither be weary of his correction;
# Proverbs 03:12
for whom Yahweh loves,
he corrects,
even as a father reproves the son in whom he delights.

# Section: Happy is the man who finds wisdom
# Proverbs 03:13
Happy is the man who finds wisdom,
the man who gets understanding.

# Proverbs 03:14
For her good profit is better than getting silver,
and her return is better than fine gold.

# Proverbs 03:15
She is more precious than rubies.

None of the things you can desire are to be compared to her.

# Proverbs 03:16
Length of days is in her right hand.

In her left hand are riches and honor.

# Proverbs 03:17
Her ways are ways of pleasantness.

All her paths are peace.

# Proverbs 03:18
She is a tree of life to those who lay hold of her.

Happy is everyone who retains her.

# Section: By wisdom Yahweh founded the earth.
# Proverbs 03:19
By wisdom Yahweh founded the earth.

By understanding,
he established the heavens.

# Proverbs 03:20
By his knowledge,
the depths were broken up,
and the skies drop down the dew.

# Section: My son
# Proverbs 03:21
My son,
let them not depart from your eyes.

Keep sound wisdom and discretion,
# Proverbs 03:22
so they will be life to your soul,
and grace for your neck.

# Proverbs 03:23
Then you shall walk in your way securely.

Your foot won’t stumble.

# Proverbs 03:24
When you lie down,
you will not be afraid.

Yes, you will lie down,
and your sleep will be sweet.

# Section: Don't be afraid of sudden fear
# Proverbs 03:25
Don't be afraid of sudden fear,
neither of the desolation of the wicked,
when it comes;
# Proverbs 03:26
for Yahweh will be your confidence,
and will keep your foot from being taken.

# Section: Don't withhold good
# Proverbs 03:27
Don't withhold good from those to whom it is due,
when it is in the power of your hand to do it.

# Proverbs 03:28
Don't say to your neighbor,
{
  Go,
  and come again;
  tomorrow I will give it to you,
}

when you have it by you.

# Section: Don't devise evil against your neighbor
# Proverbs 03:29
Don't devise evil against your neighbor,
since he dwells securely by you.

# Section: Don't strive with a man without cause
# Proverbs 03:30
Don't strive with a man without cause,
if he has done you no harm.

# Section: Don't envy the man of violence.
# Proverbs 03:31
Don't envy the man of violence.

Choose none of his ways.

# Proverbs 03:32
For the perverse is an abomination to Yahweh,
but his friendship is with the upright.

# Section: Yahweh's curse
# Proverbs 03:33
Yahweh's curse is in the house of the wicked,
but he blesses the habitation of the righteous.

# Proverbs 03:34
Surely he mocks the mockers,
but he gives grace to the humble.

# Section: The wise will inherit glory
# Proverbs 03:35
The wise will inherit glory,
but shame will be the promotion of fools.

# Section: Listen, sons
# Proverbs 04:01
Listen, sons, to a father's instruction.

Pay attention and know understanding;
# Proverbs 04:02
for I give you sound learning.

Don't forsake my law.

# Section: For I was a son to my father
# Proverbs 04:03
For I was a son to my father,
tender and an only child in the sight of my mother.

# Proverbs 04:04
He taught me,
and said to me:
{
  Let your heart retain my words.

  Keep my commandments,
  and live.

  # Proverbs 04:05
  Get wisdom.

  Get understanding.

  Don't forget,
  and don't deviate from the words of my mouth.

  # Proverbs 04:06
  Don't forsake her,
  and she will preserve you.

  Love her,
  and she will keep you.

  # Proverbs 04:07
  Wisdom is supreme.

  Get wisdom.

  Yes, though it costs all your possessions,
  get understanding.

  # Proverbs 04:08
  Esteem her,
  and she will exalt you.

  She will bring you to honor when you embrace her.

  # Proverbs 04:09
  She will give to your head a garland of grace.

  She will deliver a crown of splendor to you.
}

# Section: Listen, my son
# Proverbs 04:10
Listen, my son,
and receive my sayings.

The years of your life will be many.

# Proverbs 04:11
I have taught you in the way of wisdom.

I have led you in straight paths.

# Proverbs 04:12
When you go,
your steps will not be hampered.

When you run,
you will not stumble.

# Section: Take firm hold of instruction.
# Proverbs 04:13
Take firm hold of instruction.

Don't let her go.

Keep her,
for she is your life.

# Section: Don't enter into the path of the wicked.
# Proverbs 04:14
Don't enter into the path of the wicked.

Don't walk in the way of evil men.

  # Proverbs 04:15
  Avoid it,
  and don't pass by it.

  Turn from it,
  and pass on.

# Proverbs 04:16
For they don't sleep unless they do evil.

Their sleep is taken away,
unless they make someone fall.

# Proverbs 04:17
For they eat the bread of wickedness
and drink the wine of violence.

# Proverbs 04:18
But the path of the righteous is like the dawning light
that shines more and more until the perfect day.

# Proverbs 04:19
The way of the wicked is like darkness.

They don't know what they stumble over.

# Section: My son
# Proverbs 04:20
My son,
attend to my words.

Turn your ear to my sayings.

# Proverbs 04:21
Let them not depart from your eyes.

Keep them in the center of your heart.

# Proverbs 04:22
For they are life to those who find them,
and health to their whole body.

# Proverbs 04:23
Keep your heart with all diligence,
for out of it is the wellspring of life.

# Proverbs 04:24
Put away from yourself a perverse mouth.

Put corrupt lips far from you.

# Proverbs 04:25
Let your eyes look straight ahead.

Fix your gaze directly before you.

# Proverbs 04:26
Make the path of your feet level.

Let all of your ways be established.

# Proverbs 04:27
Don't turn to the right hand nor to the left.

Remove your foot from evil.

# Section: My son
# Proverbs 05:01
My son,
pay attention to my wisdom.

Turn your ear to my understanding,
# Proverbs 05:02
that you may maintain discretion,
that your lips may preserve knowledge.

# Proverbs 05:03
For the lips of an adulteress drip honey.

Her mouth is smoother than oil,
# Proverbs 05:04
but in the end she is as bitter as wormwood,
and as sharp as a two-edged sword.

# Proverbs 05:05
Her feet go down to death.

Her steps lead straight to Sheol.

# Proverbs 05:06
She gives no thought to the way of life.

Her ways are crooked,
and she doesn’t know it.

# Section: Now therefore, my sons, listen to me.
# Proverbs 05:07
Now therefore, my sons, listen to me.

Don't depart from the words of my mouth.

# Proverbs 05:08
Remove your way far from her.

Don't come near the door of her house,
# Proverbs 05:09
lest you give your honor to others,
and your years to the cruel one;
# Proverbs 05:10
lest strangers feast on your wealth,
and your labors enrich another man's house.

# Section: You will groan
# Proverbs 05:11
You will groan at your latter end,
when your flesh and your body are consumed,
# Proverbs 05:12
and say,
{
  How I have hated instruction,
  and my heart despised reproof.

  # Proverbs 05:13
  I haven’t obeyed the voice of my teachers,
  nor turned my ear to those who instructed me!

  # Proverbs 05:14
  I have come to the brink of utter ruin,
  among the gathered assembly.
}

# Section: Drink water out of your own cistern
# Proverbs 05:15
Drink water out of your own cistern,
running water out of your own well.

# Proverbs 05:16
Should your springs overflow in the streets,
streams of water in the public squares?

# Proverbs 05:17
Let them be for yourself alone,
not for strangers with you.

# Proverbs 05:18
Let your spring be blessed.

# Section: Rejoice in the wife of your youth.
Rejoice in the wife of your youth.

# Proverbs 05:19
A loving doe and a graceful deer ---
let her breasts satisfy you at all times.

Be captivated always with her love.

# Section: For why should you, my son
# Proverbs 05:20
For why should you, my son,
be captivated with an adulteress?

Why embrace the bosom of another?

# Proverbs 05:21
For the ways of man are before Yahweh's eyes.

He examines all his paths.

# Section: The evil deeds of the wicked ensnare him.
# Proverbs 05:22
The evil deeds of the wicked ensnare him.

The cords of his sin hold him firmly.

# Proverbs 05:23
He will die for lack of instruction.

In the greatness of his folly,
he will go astray.

# Section: My son
# Proverbs 06:01
My son,
if you have become collateral for your neighbor,
if you have struck your hands in pledge for a stranger,
# Proverbs 06:02
you are trapped by the words of your mouth;
you are ensnared with the words of your mouth.

# Proverbs 06:03
Do this now, my son, and deliver yourself,
since you have come into the hand of your neighbor.

Go, humble yourself.

Press your plea with your neighbor.

# Proverbs 06:04
Give no sleep to your eyes,
nor slumber to your eyelids.

# Proverbs 06:05
Free yourself,
like a gazelle from the hand of the hunter,
like a bird from the snare of the fowler.

# Section: Go to the ant, you sluggard.
# Proverbs 06:06
Go to the ant, you sluggard.

Consider her ways, and be wise;
# Proverbs 06:07
which having no chief, overseer, or ruler,
# Proverbs 06:08
provides her bread in the summer,
and gathers her food in the harvest.

# Section: How long will you sleep, sluggard?
# Proverbs 06:09
How long will you sleep, sluggard?

When will you arise out of your sleep?

# Proverbs 06:10
A little sleep,
a little slumber,
a little folding of the hands to sleep ---
# Proverbs 06:11
so your poverty will come as a robber,
and your scarcity as an armed man.

# Section: A worthless person
# Proverbs 06:12
A worthless person,
a man of iniquity,
is he who walks with a perverse mouth,
# Proverbs 06:13
who winks with his eyes,
who signals with his feet,
who motions with his fingers,
# Proverbs 06:14
in whose heart is perverseness,
who devises evil continually,
who always sows discord.

# Proverbs 06:15
Therefore his calamity will come suddenly.

He will be broken suddenly,
and that without remedy.

# Section: There are six things which Yahweh hates;
# Proverbs 06:16
There are six things which Yahweh hates;
yes, seven which are an abomination to him:
  # Proverbs 06:17
  arrogant eyes,
  a lying tongue,
  hands that shed innocent blood,
  # Proverbs 06:18
  a heart that devises wicked schemes,
  feet that are swift in running to mischief,
  # Proverbs 06:19
  a false witness who utters lies,
  and he who sows discord among brothers.

# Section: My son
# Proverbs 06:20
My son,
keep your father's commandment,
and don't forsake your mother's teaching.

# Proverbs 06:21
Bind them continually on your heart.

Tie them around your neck.

# Proverbs 06:22
When you walk,
it will lead you.

When you sleep,
it will watch over you.

When you awake,
it will talk with you.

# Proverbs 06:23
For the commandment is a lamp,
and the law is light.

# Section: Reproofs of instruction are the way of life
Reproofs of instruction are the way of life,
# Proverbs 06:24
to keep you from the immoral woman,
from the flattery of the wayward wife's tongue.

# Proverbs 06:25
Don't lust after her beauty in your heart,
neither let her captivate you with her eyelids.

# Proverbs 06:26
For a prostitute reduces you to a piece of bread.

The adulteress hunts for your precious life.

# Section: Can a man scoop fire into his lap?
# Proverbs 06:27
Can a man scoop fire into his lap,
and his clothes not be burned?

# Proverbs 06:28
Or can one walk on hot coals,
and his feet not be scorched?

# Proverbs 06:29
So is he who goes in to his neighbor's wife.

Whoever touches her will not be unpunished.

# Section: Men don't despise a thief if
# Proverbs 06:30
Men don't despise a thief
if he steals to satisfy himself when he is hungry,
# Proverbs 06:31
but if he is found,
he shall restore seven times.

He shall give all the wealth of his house.

# Section: He who commits adultery with a woman is void of understanding.
# Proverbs 06:32
He who commits adultery with a woman is void of understanding.

He who does it destroys his own soul.

# Proverbs 06:33
He will get wounds and dishonor.

His reproach will not be wiped away.

# Proverbs 06:34
For jealousy arouses the fury of the husband.

He won’t spare in the day of vengeance.

# Proverbs 06:35
He won’t regard any ransom,
neither will he rest content,
though you give many gifts.

# Section: My son
# Proverbs 07:01
My son, keep my words.

Lay up my commandments within you.

# Proverbs 07:02
Keep my commandments and live!

Guard my teaching as the apple of your eye.

# Proverbs 07:03
Bind them on your fingers.

Write them on the tablet of your heart.

# Proverbs 07:04
Tell wisdom,
{
  You are my sister.
}

Call understanding your relative,
# Proverbs 07:05
that they may keep you from the strange woman,
from the foreigner who flatters with her words.

# Section: For at the window of my house
# Proverbs 07:06
For at the window of my house,
I looked out through my lattice.

# Proverbs 07:07
I saw among the simple ones.

I discerned among the youths a young man void of understanding,
# Proverbs 07:08
passing through the street near her corner,
he went the way to her house,
# Proverbs 07:09
in the twilight,
in the evening of the day,
in the middle of the night and in the darkness.

# Proverbs 07:10
Behold!
There a woman met him with the attire of a prostitute,
and with crafty intent.

# Proverbs 07:11
She is loud and defiant.

Her feet don't stay in her house.

# Proverbs 07:12
Now she is in the streets,
now in the squares,
and lurking at every corner.

# Proverbs 07:13
So she caught him,
and kissed him.

# Section: With an impudent face she said to him
With an impudent face she said to him:

# Proverbs 07:14
{
  Sacrifices of peace offerings are with me.

  Today I have paid my vows.

  # Proverbs 07:15
  Therefore I came out to meet you,
  to diligently seek your face,
  and I have found you.

  # Proverbs 07:16
  I have spread my couch with carpets of tapestry,
  with striped cloths of the yarn of Egypt.

  # Proverbs 07:17
  I have perfumed my bed
  with myrrh, aloes, and cinnamon.

  # Proverbs 07:18
  Come,
  let's take our fill of loving until the morning.

  Let's solace ourselves with loving.

  # Proverbs 07:19
  For my husband isn’t at home.

  He has gone on a long journey.

  # Proverbs 07:20
  He has taken a bag of money with him.

  He will come home at the full moon.
}

# Proverbs 07:21
With persuasive words,
she led him astray.

With the flattering of her lips,
she seduced him.

# Section: He followed her immediately
# Proverbs 07:22
He followed her immediately,
as an ox goes to the slaughter,
as a fool stepping into a noose.

# Proverbs 07:23
Until an arrow strikes through his liver,
as a bird hurries to the snare,
and doesn’t know that it will cost his life.

# Section: Now therefore, sons, listen to me.
# Proverbs 07:24
Now therefore, sons, listen to me.

Pay attention to the words of my mouth.

# Proverbs 07:25
Don't let your heart turn to her ways.

Don't go astray in her paths,
# Proverbs 07:26
for she has thrown down many wounded.

Yes, all her slain are a mighty army.

# Proverbs 07:27
Her house is the way to Sheol,
going down to the rooms of death.

# Section: Doesn’t wisdom cry out?
# Proverbs 08:01
Doesn’t wisdom cry out?

Doesn’t understanding raise her voice?

# Proverbs 08:02
On the top of high places by the way,
where the paths meet, she stands.

# Proverbs 08:03
Beside the gates,
at the entry of the city,
at the entry doors,
she cries aloud:

# Proverbs 08:04
{
  I call to you men!

  I send my voice to the sons of mankind.

  # Proverbs 08:05
  You simple,
  understand prudence!

  You fools,
  be of an understanding heart!

  # Proverbs 08:06
  Hear,
  for I will speak excellent things.

  The opening of my lips is for right things.

  # Proverbs 08:07
  For my mouth speaks truth.

  Wickedness is an abomination to my lips.

  # Proverbs 08:08
  All the words of my mouth are in righteousness.

  There is nothing crooked or perverse in them.

  # Proverbs 08:09
  They are all plain to him who understands,
  right to those who find knowledge.

  # Proverbs 08:10
  Receive my instruction rather than silver,
  knowledge rather than choice gold.

  # Proverbs 08:11
  For wisdom is better than rubies.

  All the things that may be desired can’t be compared to it.
}

# Section:   I, wisdom
{
  # Proverbs 08:12
  I, wisdom,
  have made prudence my dwelling.

  Find out knowledge and discretion.

  # Proverbs 08:13
  The fear of Yahweh is to hate evil.

  I hate pride, arrogance, the evil way,
  and the perverse mouth.

  # Proverbs 08:14
  Counsel and sound knowledge are mine.

  I have understanding and power.

  # Proverbs 08:15
  By me kings reign,
  and princes decree justice.

  # Proverbs 08:16
  By me princes rule,
  nobles,
  and all the righteous rulers of the earth.

  # Proverbs 08:17
  I love those who love me.

  Those who seek me diligently will find me.

  # Proverbs 08:18
  With me are riches,
  honor,
  enduring wealth,
  and prosperity.

  # Proverbs 08:19
  My fruit is better than gold,
  yes, than fine gold,
  my yield than choice silver.

  # Proverbs 08:20
  I walk in the way of righteousness,
  in the middle of the paths of justice,
  # Proverbs 08:21
  that I may give wealth to those who love me.

  I fill their treasuries.
}

# Section: Yahweh possessed me in the beginning
{
  # Proverbs 08:22
  Yahweh possessed me in the beginning of his work,
  before his deeds of old.

  # Proverbs 08:23
  I was set up from everlasting,
  from the beginning,
  before the earth existed.

  # Proverbs 08:24
  When there were no depths,
  I was born,
  when there were no springs abounding with water.

  # Proverbs 08:25
  Before the mountains were settled in place,
  before the hills,
  I was born;
  # Proverbs 08:26
  while as yet he had not made the earth,
  nor the fields,
  nor the beginning of the dust of the world.

  # Proverbs 08:27
  When he established the heavens,
  I was there.

  When he set a circle on the surface of the deep,
  # Proverbs 08:28
  when he established the clouds above,
  when the springs of the deep became strong,
  # Proverbs 08:29
  when he gave to the sea its boundary,
  that the waters should not violate his commandment,
  when he marked out the foundations of the earth,
  # Proverbs 08:30
  then I was the craftsman by his side.

  I was a delight day by day,
  always rejoicing before him,
  # Proverbs 08:31
  rejoicing in his whole world.

  My delight was with the sons of men.
}

# Section:   Now therefore, my sons, listen to me
{
  # Proverbs 08:32
  Now therefore, my sons, listen to me,
  for blessed are those who keep my ways.

  # Proverbs 08:33
  Hear instruction,
  and be wise.

  Don't refuse it.

  # Proverbs 08:34
  Blessed is the man who hears me,
  watching daily at my gates,
  waiting at my door posts.

  # Proverbs 08:35
  For whoever finds me finds life,
  and will obtain favor from Yahweh.

  # Proverbs 08:36
  But he who sins against me wrongs his own soul.

  All those who hate me love death.
}

# Section: Wisdom has built her house.
# Proverbs 09:01
Wisdom has built her house.

She has carved out her seven pillars.

# Proverbs 09:02
She has prepared her meat.

She has mixed her wine.

She has also set her table.

# Proverbs 09:03
She has sent out her maidens.

She cries from the highest places of the city:

# Proverbs 09:04
{
  Whoever is simple,
  let him turn in here!
}

As for him who is void of understanding,
she says to him,

# Proverbs 09:05
{
  Come, eat some of my bread,
  Drink some of the wine which I have mixed!

  # Proverbs 09:06
  Leave your simple ways, and live.

  Walk in the way of understanding.
}

# Section: One who corrects a mocker invites insult.
# Proverbs 09:07
One who corrects a mocker invites insult.

One who reproves a wicked man invites abuse.

# Proverbs 09:08
Don't reprove a scoffer,
lest he hate you.

# Section: Reprove a wise person
Reprove a wise person,
and he will love you.

# Proverbs 09:09
Instruct a wise person,
and he will be still wiser.

Teach a righteous person,
and he will increase in learning.

# Section: The fear of Yahweh is the beginning of wisdom.
# Proverbs 09:10
The fear of Yahweh is the beginning of wisdom.

The knowledge of the Holy One is understanding.

# Proverbs 09:11
For by me your days will be multiplied.

The years of your life will be increased.

# Proverbs 09:12
If you are wise,
you are wise for yourself.

If you mock,
you alone will bear it.

# Section: The foolish woman is loud
# Proverbs 09:13
The foolish woman is loud,
undisciplined,
and knows nothing.

# Proverbs 09:14
She sits at the door of her house,
on a seat in the high places of the city,
# Proverbs 09:15
to call to those who pass by,
who go straight on their ways,
# Proverbs 09:16
{
  Whoever is simple,
  let him turn in here.
}

As for him who is void of understanding,
she says to him,
{
  # Proverbs 09:17
  Stolen water is sweet.

  Food eaten in secret is pleasant.
}

# Proverbs 09:18
But he doesn’t know that the departed spirits are there,
that her guests are in the depths of Sheol.

# Section: The proverbs of Solomon.
# Proverbs 10:01
The proverbs of Solomon.

A wise son makes a glad father;
but a foolish son brings grief to his mother.

# Section: Treasures of wickedness profit nothing
# Proverbs 10:02
Treasures of wickedness profit nothing,
but righteousness delivers from death.

# Section: Yahweh will not allow
# Proverbs 10:03
Yahweh will not allow the soul of the righteous to go hungry,
but he thrusts away the desire of the wicked.

# Section: He becomes poor
# Proverbs 10:04
He becomes poor who works with a lazy hand,
but the hand of the diligent brings wealth.

# Section: He who gathers in summer
# Proverbs 10:05
He who gathers in summer is a wise son,
but he who sleeps during the harvest is a son who causes shame.

# Section: Blessings are on the head of the righteous
# Proverbs 10:06
Blessings are on the head of the righteous,
but violence covers the mouth of the wicked.

# Section: The memory of the righteous
# Proverbs 10:07
The memory of the righteous is blessed,
but the name of the wicked will rot.

# Section: The wise in heart accept commandments
# Proverbs 10:08
The wise in heart accept commandments,
but a chattering fool will fall.

# Section: He who walks blamelessly
# Proverbs 10:09
He who walks blamelessly walks surely,
but he who perverts his ways will be found out.

# Section: One who winks with the eye
# Proverbs 10:10
One who winks with the eye causes sorrow,
but a chattering fool will fall.

# Section: The mouth of the righteous
# Proverbs 10:11
The mouth of the righteous is a spring of life,
but violence covers the mouth of the wicked.

# Section: Hatred stirs up strife
# Proverbs 10:12
Hatred stirs up strife,
but love covers all wrongs.

# Section: Wisdom is found
# Proverbs 10:13
Wisdom is found on the lips of him who has discernment,
but a rod is for the back of him who is void of understanding.

# Section: Wise men lay up knowledge,
# Proverbs 10:14
Wise men lay up knowledge,
but the mouth of the foolish is near ruin.

# Section: The rich man's wealth
# Proverbs 10:15
The rich man's wealth is his strong city.
The destruction of the poor is their poverty.

# Section: The labor of the righteous
# Proverbs 10:16
The labor of the righteous leads to life.
The increase of the wicked leads to sin.

# Section: He is in the way of life
# Proverbs 10:17
He is in the way of life who heeds correction,
but he who forsakes reproof leads others astray.

# Section: He who hides hatred
# Proverbs 10:18
He who hides hatred has lying lips.
He who utters a slander is a fool.

# Section: In the multitude of words
# Proverbs 10:19
In the multitude of words there is no lack of disobedience,
but he who restrains his lips does wisely.

# Section: The tongue of the righteous
# Proverbs 10:20
The tongue of the righteous is like choice silver.
The heart of the wicked is of little worth.

# Section: The lips of the righteous
# Proverbs 10:21
The lips of the righteous feed many,
but the foolish die for lack of understanding.

# Section: Yahweh's blessing brings wealth
# Proverbs 10:22
Yahweh's blessing brings wealth,
and he adds no trouble to it.

# Section: It is a fool's pleasure
# Proverbs 10:23
It is a fool's pleasure to do wickedness,
but wisdom is a man of understanding's pleasure.

# Section: What the wicked fear
# Proverbs 10:24
What the wicked fear will overtake them,
but the desire of the righteous will be granted.

# Section: When the whirlwind passes
# Proverbs 10:25
When the whirlwind passes,
the wicked is no more;
but the righteous stand firm forever.

# Section: As vinegar to the teeth,
# Proverbs 10:26
As vinegar to the teeth,
and as smoke to the eyes,
so is the sluggard to those who send him.

# Section: The fear of Yahweh prolongs days
# Proverbs 10:27
The fear of Yahweh prolongs days,
but the years of the wicked shall be shortened.

# Section: The prospect of the righteous
# Proverbs 10:28
The prospect of the righteous is joy,
but the hope of the wicked will perish.

# Section: The way of Yahweh
# Proverbs 10:29
The way of Yahweh is a stronghold to the upright,
but it is a destruction to the workers of iniquity.

# Section: The righteous
# Proverbs 10:30
The righteous will never be removed,
but the wicked will not dwell in the land.

# Section: The mouth of the righteous
# Proverbs 10:31
The mouth of the righteous produces wisdom,
but the perverse tongue will be cut off.

# Section: The lips of the righteous
# Proverbs 10:32
The lips of the righteous know what is acceptable,
but the mouth of the wicked is perverse.

# Section: A false balance is an abomination to Yahweh
# Proverbs 11:01
A false balance is an abomination to Yahweh,
but accurate weights are his delight.

# Section: When pride comes
# Proverbs 11:02
When pride comes, then comes shame,
but with humility comes wisdom.

# Section: The integrity of the upright
# Proverbs 11:03
The integrity of the upright shall guide them,
but the perverseness of the treacherous shall destroy them.

# Section: Riches don't profit in the day of wrath
# Proverbs 11:04
Riches don't profit in the day of wrath,
but righteousness delivers from death.

# Section: The righteousness of the blameless
# Proverbs 11:05
The righteousness of the blameless will direct his way,
but the wicked shall fall by his own wickedness.

# Section: The righteousness of the upright
# Proverbs 11:06
The righteousness of the upright shall deliver them,
but the unfaithful will be trapped by evil desires.

# Section: When a wicked man dies
# Proverbs 11:07
When a wicked man dies, hope perishes,
and expectation of power comes to nothing.

# Section: A righteous person
# Proverbs 11:08
A righteous person is delivered out of trouble,
and the wicked takes his place.

# Section: With his mouth the godless man
# Proverbs 11:09
With his mouth the godless man destroys his neighbor,
but the righteous will be delivered through knowledge.

# Section: When it goes well with the righteous
# Proverbs 11:10
When it goes well with the righteous, the city rejoices.
When the wicked perish, there is shouting.

# Section: By the blessing of the upright
# Proverbs 11:11
By the blessing of the upright, the city is exalted,
but it is overthrown by the mouth of the wicked.

# Section: One who despises his neighbor
# Proverbs 11:12
One who despises his neighbor is void of wisdom,
but a man of understanding holds his peace.

# Section: One who brings gossip
# Proverbs 11:13
One who brings gossip betrays a confidence,
but one who is of a trustworthy spirit is one who keeps a secret.

# Section: Where there is no wise guidance
# Proverbs 11:14
Where there is no wise guidance, the nation falls,
but in the multitude of counselors there is victory.

# Section: He who is collateral for a stranger
# Proverbs 11:15
He who is collateral for a stranger will suffer for it,
but he who refuses pledges of collateral is secure.

# Section: A gracious woman
# Proverbs 11:16
A gracious woman obtains honor,
but violent men obtain riches.

# Section: The merciful man
# Proverbs 11:17
The merciful man does good to his own soul,
but he who is cruel troubles his own flesh.

# Section: Wicked people
# Proverbs 11:18
Wicked people earn deceitful wages,
but one who sows righteousness reaps a sure reward.

# Section: He who is truly righteous
# Proverbs 11:19
He who is truly righteous gets life.
He who pursues evil gets death.

# Section: Those who are perverse in heart
# Proverbs 11:20
Those who are perverse in heart are an abomination to Yahweh,
but those whose ways are blameless are his delight.

# Section: Most certainly, the evil man
# Proverbs 11:21
Most certainly, the evil man will not be unpunished,
but the offspring of the righteous will be delivered.

# Section: Like a gold ring in a pig's snout
# Proverbs 11:22
Like a gold ring in a pig's snout,
is a beautiful woman who lacks discretion.

# Section: The desire of the righteous
# Proverbs 11:23
The desire of the righteous is only good.
The expectation of the wicked is wrath.

# Section: There is one who scatters
# Proverbs 11:24
There is one who scatters,
  and increases yet more.
There is one who withholds more than is appropriate,
  but gains poverty.

# Section: The liberal soul
# Proverbs 11:25
The liberal soul shall be made fat.
He who waters shall also be watered himself.

# Section: People curse someone who withholds grain
# Proverbs 11:26
People curse someone who withholds grain,
but blessing will be on the head of him who sells it.

# Section: He who diligently seeks good
# Proverbs 11:27
He who diligently seeks good seeks favor,
but he who searches after evil,
it shall come to him.

# Section: He who trusts in his riches
# Proverbs 11:28
He who trusts in his riches will fall,
but the righteous shall flourish as the green leaf.

# Section: He who troubles his own house shall inherit the wind.
# Proverbs 11:29
He who troubles his own house shall inherit the wind.
The foolish shall be servant to the wise of heart.

# Section: The fruit of the righteous
# Proverbs 11:30
The fruit of the righteous is a tree of life.

# Section: He who is wise wins souls.
He who is wise wins souls.

# Section: Behold! The righteous
# Proverbs 11:31
Behold! The righteous shall be repaid in the earth,
how much more the wicked and the sinner!

# Section: Whoever loves correction loves knowledge
# Proverbs 12:01
Whoever loves correction loves knowledge,
but he who hates reproof is stupid.

# Section: A good man
# Proverbs 12:02
A good man shall obtain favor from Yahweh,
but he will condemn a man of wicked plans.

# Section: A man shall not be established by wickedness
# Proverbs 12:03
A man shall not be established by wickedness,
but the root of the righteous shall not be moved.

# Section: A worthy woman
# Proverbs 12:04
A worthy woman is the crown of her husband,
but a disgraceful wife is as rottenness in his bones.

# Section: The thoughts of the righteous
# Proverbs 12:05
The thoughts of the righteous are just,
but the advice of the wicked is deceitful.

# Section: The words of the wicked
# Proverbs 12:06
The words of the wicked are about lying in wait for blood,
but the speech of the upright rescues them.

# Section: The wicked
# Proverbs 12:07
The wicked are overthrown, and are no more,
but the house of the righteous shall stand.

# Section: A man shall be commended
# Proverbs 12:08
A man shall be commended according to his wisdom,
but he who has a warped mind shall be despised.

# Section: Better is he who is little known
# Proverbs 12:09
Better is he who is little known, and has a servant,
than he who honors himself and lacks bread.

# Section: A righteous man
# Proverbs 12:10
A righteous man respects the life of his animal,
but the tender mercies of the wicked are cruel.

# Section: He who tills his land
# Proverbs 12:11
He who tills his land shall have plenty of bread,
but he who chases fantasies is void of understanding.

# Section: The wicked
# Proverbs 12:12
The wicked desires the plunder of evil men,
but the root of the righteous flourishes.

# Section: An evil man
# Proverbs 12:13
An evil man is trapped by sinfulness of lips,
but the righteous shall come out of trouble.

# Section: A man shall be satisfied
# Proverbs 12:14
A man shall be satisfied with good by the fruit of his mouth.
The work of a man's hands shall be rewarded to him.

# Section: The way of a fool
# Proverbs 12:15
The way of a fool is right in his own eyes,
but he who is wise listens to counsel.

# Section: A fool
# Proverbs 12:16
A fool shows his annoyance the same day,
but one who overlooks an insult is prudent.

# Section: He who is truthful
# Proverbs 12:17
He who is truthful testifies honestly,
but a false witness lies.

# Section: There is one who speaks rashly
# Proverbs 12:18
There is one who speaks rashly like the piercing of a sword,
but the tongue of the wise heals.

# Section: Truth's lips
# Proverbs 12:19
Truth's lips will be established forever,
but a lying tongue is only momentary.

# Section: Deceit
# Proverbs 12:20
Deceit is in the heart of those who plot evil,
but joy comes to the promoters of peace.

# Section: No mischief shall happen to the righteous
# Proverbs 12:21
No mischief shall happen to the righteous,
but the wicked shall be filled with evil.

# Section: Lying lips
# Proverbs 12:22
Lying lips are an abomination to Yahweh,
but those who do the truth are his delight.

# Section: A prudent man
# Proverbs 12:23
A prudent man keeps his knowledge,
but the hearts of fools proclaim foolishness.

# Section: The hands of the diligent ones
# Proverbs 12:24
The hands of the diligent ones shall rule,
but laziness ends in slave labor.

# Section: Anxiety in a man's heart
# Proverbs 12:25
Anxiety in a man's heart weighs it down,
but a kind word makes it glad.

# Section: A righteous person
# Proverbs 12:26
A righteous person is cautious in friendship,
but the way of the wicked leads them astray.

# Section: The slothful man
# Proverbs 12:27
The slothful man doesn’t roast his game,
but the possessions of diligent men are prized.

# Section: In the way of righteousness
# Proverbs 12:28
In the way of righteousness is life;
in its path there is no death.

# Section: A wise son
# Proverbs 13:01
A wise son listens to his father's instruction,
but a scoffer doesn’t listen to rebuke.

# Section: By the fruit of his lips
# Proverbs 13:02
By the fruit of his lips,
a man enjoys good things,
but the unfaithful crave violence.

# Section: He who guards his mouth
# Proverbs 13:03
He who guards his mouth guards his soul.
One who opens wide his lips comes to ruin.

# Section: The soul of the sluggard
# Proverbs 13:04
The soul of the sluggard desires,
and has nothing,
but the desire of the diligent shall be fully satisfied.

# Section: A righteous man
# Proverbs 13:05
A righteous man hates lies,
but a wicked man brings shame and disgrace.

# Section: Righteousness
# Proverbs 13:06
Righteousness guards the way of integrity,
but wickedness overthrows the sinner.

# Section: There are some who pretend to be rich
# Proverbs 13:07
There are some who pretend to be rich,
  yet have nothing.
There are some who pretend to be poor,
  yet have great wealth.

# Section: The ransom of a man's life
# Proverbs 13:08
The ransom of a man's life is his riches,
but the poor hear no threats.

# Section: The light of the righteous
# Proverbs 13:09
The light of the righteous shines brightly,
but the lamp of the wicked is snuffed out.

# Section: Pride
# Proverbs 13:10
Pride only breeds quarrels,
but wisdom is with people who take advice.

# Section: Wealth gained dishonestly
# Proverbs 13:11
Wealth gained dishonestly dwindles away,
but he who gathers by hand makes it grow.

# Section: Hope deferred
# Proverbs 13:12
Hope deferred makes the heart sick,
but when longing is fulfilled,
it is a tree of life.

# Section: Whoever despises instruction
# Proverbs 13:13
Whoever despises instruction will pay for it,
but he who respects a command will be rewarded.

# Section: The teaching of the wise
# Proverbs 13:14
The teaching of the wise is a spring of life,
to turn from the snares of death.

# Section: Good understanding
# Proverbs 13:15
Good understanding wins favor,
but the way of the unfaithful is hard.

# Section: Every prudent man
# Proverbs 13:16
Every prudent man acts from knowledge,
but a fool exposes folly.

# Section: A wicked messenger
# Proverbs 13:17
A wicked messenger falls into trouble,
but a trustworthy envoy gains healing.

# Section: Poverty and shame
# Proverbs 13:18
Poverty and shame come to him who refuses discipline,
but he who heeds correction shall be honored.

# Section: Longing fulfilled
# Proverbs 13:19
Longing fulfilled is sweet to the soul,
but fools detest turning from evil.

# Section: One who walks with wise men
# Proverbs 13:20
One who walks with wise men grows wise,
but a companion of fools suffers harm.

# Section: Misfortune pursues
# Proverbs 13:21
Misfortune pursues sinners,
but prosperity rewards the righteous.

# Section: A good man leaves an inheritance
# Proverbs 13:22
A good man leaves an inheritance to his children's children,
but the wealth of the sinner is stored for the righteous.

# Section: An abundance of food
# Proverbs 13:23
An abundance of food is in poor people's fields,
but injustice sweeps it away.

# Section: One who spares the rod
# Proverbs 13:24
One who spares the rod hates his son,
but one who loves him is careful to discipline him.

# Section: The righteous one eats
# Proverbs 13:25
The righteous one eats to the satisfying of his soul,
but the belly of the wicked goes hungry.

# Section: Every wise woman
# Proverbs 14:01
Every wise woman builds her house,
but the foolish one tears it down with her own hands.

# Section: He who walks in his uprightness
# Proverbs 14:02
He who walks in his uprightness fears Yahweh,
but he who is perverse in his ways despises him.

# Section: The fool's talk
# Proverbs 14:03
The fool's talk brings a rod to his back,
but the lips of the wise protect them.

# Section: Where no oxen are
# Proverbs 14:04
Where no oxen are,
the crib is clean,
but much increase is by the strength of the ox.

# Section: A truthful witness
# Proverbs 14:05
A truthful witness will not lie,
but a false witness pours out lies.

# Section: A scoffer
# Proverbs 14:06
A scoffer seeks wisdom,
and doesn’t find it,
but knowledge comes easily to a discerning person.

# Section: Stay away from a foolish man
# Proverbs 14:07
Stay away from a foolish man,
for you won’t find knowledge on his lips.

# Section: The wisdom of the prudent is to think about his way,
# Proverbs 14:08
The wisdom of the prudent is to think about his way,
but the folly of fools is deceit.

# Section: Fools mock at making atonement for sins,
# Proverbs 14:09
Fools mock at making atonement for sins,
but among the upright there is good will.

# Section: The heart knows its own bitterness and joy;
# Proverbs 14:10
The heart knows its own bitterness and joy;
he will not share these with a stranger.

# Section: The house of the wicked will be overthrown,
# Proverbs 14:11
The house of the wicked will be overthrown,
but the tent of the upright will flourish.

# Section: There is a way which seems right to a man,
# Proverbs 14:12
There is a way which seems right to a man,
but in the end it leads to death.

# Section: Even in laughter the heart may be sorrowful,
# Proverbs 14:13
Even in laughter the heart may be sorrowful,
and mirth may end in heaviness.

# Section: The unfaithful will be repaid for his own ways;
# Proverbs 14:14
The unfaithful will be repaid for his own ways;
likewise a good man will be rewarded for his ways.

# Section: A simple man believes everything,
# Proverbs 14:15
A simple man believes everything,
but the prudent man carefully considers his ways.

# Section: A wise man fears and shuns evil,
# Proverbs 14:16
A wise man fears and shuns evil,
but the fool is hot headed and reckless.

# Section: He who is quick to become angry will commit folly,
# Proverbs 14:17
He who is quick to become angry will commit folly,
and a crafty man is hated.

# Section: The simple inherit folly,
# Proverbs 14:18
The simple inherit folly,
but the prudent are crowned with knowledge.

# Section: The evil bow down before the good,
# Proverbs 14:19
The evil bow down before the good,
and the wicked at the gates of the righteous.

# Section: The poor person is shunned even by his own neighbor,
# Proverbs 14:20
The poor person is shunned even by his own neighbor,
but the rich person has many friends.

# Section: He who despises his neighbor sins,
# Proverbs 14:21
He who despises his neighbor sins,
but he who has pity on the poor is blessed.

# Section: Don't they go astray who plot evil?
# Proverbs 14:22
Don't they go astray who plot evil?
But love and faithfulness belong to those who plan good.

# Section: In all hard work there is profit,
# Proverbs 14:23
In all hard work there is profit,
but the talk of the lips leads only to poverty.

# Section: The crown of the wise is their riches,
# Proverbs 14:24
The crown of the wise is their riches,
but the folly of fools crowns them with folly.

# Section: A truthful witness saves souls,
# Proverbs 14:25
A truthful witness saves souls,
but a false witness is deceitful.

# Section: In the fear of Yahweh is a secure fortress,
# Proverbs 14:26
In the fear of Yahweh is a secure fortress,
and he will be a refuge for his children.

# Section: The fear of Yahweh is a fountain of life,
# Proverbs 14:27
The fear of Yahweh is a fountain of life,
turning people from the snares of death.

# Section: In the multitude of people is the king's glory,
# Proverbs 14:28
In the multitude of people is the king's glory,
but in the lack of people is the destruction of the prince.

# Section: He who is slow to anger has great understanding,
# Proverbs 14:29
He who is slow to anger has great understanding,
but he who has a quick temper displays folly.

# Section: The life of the body is a heart at peace,
# Proverbs 14:30
The life of the body is a heart at peace,
but envy rots the bones.

# Section: He who oppresses the poor shows contempt for his Maker,
# Proverbs 14:31
He who oppresses the poor shows contempt for his Maker,
but he who is kind to the needy honors him.

# Section: The wicked is brought down in his calamity,
# Proverbs 14:32
The wicked is brought down in his calamity,
but in death,
the righteous has a refuge.

# Section: Wisdom rests in the heart of one who has understanding,
# Proverbs 14:33
Wisdom rests in the heart of one who has understanding,
and is even made known in the inward part of fools.

# Section: Righteousness exalts a nation,
# Proverbs 14:34
Righteousness exalts a nation,
but sin is a disgrace to any people.

# Section: The king's favor is toward a servant who deals wisely,
# Proverbs 14:35
The king's favor is toward a servant who deals wisely,
but his wrath is toward one who causes shame.

# Section: A gentle answer turns away wrath,
# Proverbs 15:01
A gentle answer turns away wrath,
but a harsh word stirs up anger.

# Section: The tongue of the wise commends knowledge,
# Proverbs 15:02
The tongue of the wise commends knowledge,
but the mouths of fools gush out folly.

# Section: Yahweh's eyes are everywhere,
# Proverbs 15:03
Yahweh's eyes are everywhere,
keeping watch on the evil and the good.

# Section: A gentle tongue is a tree of life,
# Proverbs 15:04
A gentle tongue is a tree of life,
but deceit in it crushes the spirit.

# Section: A fool despises his father's correction,
# Proverbs 15:05
A fool despises his father's correction,
but he who heeds reproof shows prudence.

# Section: In the house of the righteous is much treasure,
# Proverbs 15:06
In the house of the righteous is much treasure,
but the income of the wicked brings trouble.

# Section: The lips of the wise spread knowledge;
# Proverbs 15:07
The lips of the wise spread knowledge;
not so with the heart of fools.

# Section: The sacrifice made by the wicked is an abomination to Yahweh,
# Proverbs 15:08
The sacrifice made by the wicked is an abomination to Yahweh,
but the prayer of the upright is his delight.

# Section: The way of the wicked is an abomination to Yahweh,
# Proverbs 15:09
The way of the wicked is an abomination to Yahweh,
but he loves him who follows after righteousness.

# Section: There is stern discipline for one who forsakes the way.
# Proverbs 15:10
There is stern discipline for one who forsakes the way.
Whoever hates reproof shall die.

# Section: Sheol and Abaddon are before Yahweh ---
# Proverbs 15:11
Sheol and Abaddon are before Yahweh ---
how much more then the hearts of the children of men!

# Section: A scoffer doesn’t love to be reproved;
# Proverbs 15:12
A scoffer doesn’t love to be reproved;
he will not go to the wise.

# Section: A glad heart makes a cheerful face,
# Proverbs 15:13
A glad heart makes a cheerful face,
but an aching heart breaks the spirit.

# Section: The heart of one who has understanding seeks knowledge,
# Proverbs 15:14
The heart of one who has understanding seeks knowledge,
but the mouths of fools feed on folly.

# Section: All the days of the afflicted are wretched,
# Proverbs 15:15
All the days of the afflicted are wretched,
but one who has a cheerful heart enjoys a continual feast.

# Section: Better is little,
# Proverbs 15:16
Better is little,
with the fear of Yahweh,
than great treasure with trouble.

# Section: Better is a dinner of herbs,
# Proverbs 15:17
Better is a dinner of herbs,
where love is,
than a fattened calf with hatred.

# Section: A wrathful man stirs up contention,
# Proverbs 15:18
A wrathful man stirs up contention,
but one who is slow to anger appeases strife.

# Section: The way of the sluggard is like a thorn patch,
# Proverbs 15:19
The way of the sluggard is like a thorn patch,
but the path of the upright is a highway.

# Section: A wise son makes a father glad,
# Proverbs 15:20
A wise son makes a father glad,
but a foolish man despises his mother.

# Section: Folly is joy to one who is void of wisdom,
# Proverbs 15:21
Folly is joy to one who is void of wisdom,
but a man of understanding keeps his way straight.

# Section: Where there is no counsel,
# Proverbs 15:22
Where there is no counsel,
plans fail;
but in a multitude of counselors they are established.

# Section: Joy comes to a man with the reply of his mouth.
# Proverbs 15:23
Joy comes to a man with the reply of his mouth.
How good is a word at the right time!

# Proverbs 15:24
The path of life leads upward for the wise,
to keep him from going downward to Sheol.

# Section: Yahweh will uproot the house of the proud,
# Proverbs 15:25
Yahweh will uproot the house of the proud,
but he will keep the widow's borders intact.

# Section: Yahweh detests the thoughts of the wicked,
# Proverbs 15:26
Yahweh detests the thoughts of the wicked,
but the thoughts of the pure are pleasing.

# Section: He who is greedy for gain troubles his own house,
# Proverbs 15:27
He who is greedy for gain troubles his own house,
but he who hates bribes will live.

# Section: The heart of the righteous weighs answers,
# Proverbs 15:28
The heart of the righteous weighs answers,
but the mouth of the wicked gushes out evil.

# Section: Yahweh is far from the wicked,
# Proverbs 15:29
Yahweh is far from the wicked,
but he hears the prayer of the righteous.

# Section: The light of the eyes rejoices the heart.
# Proverbs 15:30
The light of the eyes rejoices the heart.
Good news gives health to the bones.

# Section: The ear that listens to reproof lives,
# Proverbs 15:31
The ear that listens to reproof lives,
and will be at home among the wise.

# Section: He who refuses correction despises his own soul,
# Proverbs 15:32
He who refuses correction despises his own soul,
but he who listens to reproof gets understanding.

# Section: The fear of Yahweh teaches wisdom.
# Proverbs 15:33
The fear of Yahweh teaches wisdom.
Before honor is humility.

# Section: The plans of the heart belong to man,
# Proverbs 16:01
The plans of the heart belong to man,
but the answer of the tongue is from Yahweh.

# Section: All the ways of a man are clean in his own eyes,
# Proverbs 16:02
All the ways of a man are clean in his own eyes,
but Yahweh weighs the motives.

# Section: Commit your deeds to Yahweh,
# Proverbs 16:03
Commit your deeds to Yahweh,
and your plans shall succeed.

# Section: Yahweh has made everything for its own end ---  yes,
# Proverbs 16:04
Yahweh has made everything for its own end ---  yes,
even the wicked for the day of evil.

# Section: Everyone who is proud in heart is an abomination to Yahweh;
# Proverbs 16:05
Everyone who is proud in heart is an abomination to Yahweh;
they shall certainly not be unpunished.

# Section: By mercy and truth iniquity is atoned for.
# Proverbs 16:06
By mercy and truth iniquity is atoned for.
By the fear of Yahweh men depart from evil.

# Section: When a man's ways please Yahweh,
# Proverbs 16:07
When a man's ways please Yahweh,
he makes even his enemies to be at peace with him.

# Section: Better is a little with righteousness,
# Proverbs 16:08
Better is a little with righteousness,
than great revenues with injustice.

# Section: A man's heart plans his course,
# Proverbs 16:09
A man's heart plans his course,
but Yahweh directs his steps.

# Section: Inspired judgments are on the lips of the king.
# Proverbs 16:10
Inspired judgments are on the lips of the king.
He shall not betray his mouth.

# Section: Honest balances and scales are Yahweh's;
# Proverbs 16:11
Honest balances and scales are Yahweh's;
all the weights in the bag are his work.

# Section: It is an abomination for kings to do wrong,
# Proverbs 16:12
It is an abomination for kings to do wrong,
for the throne is established by righteousness.

# Section: Righteous lips are the delight of kings.
# Proverbs 16:13
Righteous lips are the delight of kings.
They value one who speaks the truth.

# Section: The king's wrath is a messenger of death,
# Proverbs 16:14
The king's wrath is a messenger of death,
but a wise man will pacify it.

# Section: In the light of the king's face is life.
# Proverbs 16:15
In the light of the king's face is life.
His favor is like a cloud of the spring rain.

# Section: How much better it is to get wisdom than gold!
# Proverbs 16:16
How much better it is to get wisdom than gold!
Yes, to get understanding is to be chosen rather than silver.

# Section: The highway of the upright is to depart from evil.
# Proverbs 16:17
The highway of the upright is to depart from evil.
He who keeps his way preserves his soul.

# Section: Pride goes before destruction,
# Proverbs 16:18
Pride goes before destruction,
and an arrogant spirit before a fall.

# Section: It is better to be of a lowly spirit with the poor,
# Proverbs 16:19
It is better to be of a lowly spirit with the poor,
than to divide the plunder with the proud.

# Section: He who heeds the Word finds prosperity.
# Proverbs 16:20
He who heeds the Word finds prosperity.
Whoever trusts in Yahweh is blessed.

# Section: The wise in heart shall be called prudent.
# Proverbs 16:21
The wise in heart shall be called prudent.
Pleasantness of the lips promotes instruction.

# Section: Understanding is a fountain of life to one who has it,
# Proverbs 16:22
Understanding is a fountain of life to one who has it,
but the punishment of fools is their folly.

# Section: The heart of the wise instructs his mouth,
# Proverbs 16:23
The heart of the wise instructs his mouth,
and adds learning to his lips.

# Section: Pleasant words are a honeycomb,
# Proverbs 16:24
Pleasant words are a honeycomb,
sweet to the soul,
and health to the bones.

# Section: There is a way which seems right to a man,
# Proverbs 16:25
There is a way which seems right to a man,
but in the end it leads to death.

# Section: The appetite of the laboring man labors for him,
# Proverbs 16:26
The appetite of the laboring man labors for him,
for his mouth urges him on.

# Section: A worthless man devises mischief.
# Proverbs 16:27
A worthless man devises mischief.
His speech is like a scorching fire.

# Section: A perverse man stirs up strife.
# Proverbs 16:28
A perverse man stirs up strife.
A whisperer separates close friends.

# Section: A man of violence entices his neighbor,
# Proverbs 16:29
A man of violence entices his neighbor,
and leads him in a way that is not good.

# Section: One who winks his eyes to plot perversities,
# Proverbs 16:30
One who winks his eyes to plot perversities,
one who compresses his lips,
is bent on evil.

# Section: Gray hair is a crown of glory.
# Proverbs 16:31
Gray hair is a crown of glory.

It is attained by a life of righteousness.

# Section: One who is slow to anger is better than the mighty;
# Proverbs 16:32
One who is slow to anger is better than the mighty;
one who rules his spirit,
than he who takes a city.

# Section: The lot is cast into the lap,
# Proverbs 16:33
The lot is cast into the lap,
but its every decision is from Yahweh.

# Section: Better is a dry morsel with quietness,
# Proverbs 17:01
Better is a dry morsel with quietness,
than a house full of feasting with strife.

# Section: A servant who deals wisely will rule over a son who causes shame,
# Proverbs 17:02
A servant who deals wisely will rule over a son who causes shame,
and shall have a part in the inheritance among the brothers.

# Section: The refining pot is for silver,
# Proverbs 17:03
The refining pot is for silver,
and the furnace for gold,
but Yahweh tests the hearts.

# Section: An evildoer heeds wicked lips.
# Proverbs 17:04
An evildoer heeds wicked lips.

A liar gives ear to a mischievous tongue.

# Section: Whoever mocks the poor reproaches his Maker.
# Proverbs 17:05
Whoever mocks the poor reproaches his Maker.

He who is glad at calamity shall not be unpunished.

# Section: Children's children are the crown of old men;
# Proverbs 17:06
Children's children are the crown of old men;
the glory of children is their parents.

# Section: Excellent speech isn’t fitting for a fool,
# Proverbs 17:07
Excellent speech isn’t fitting for a fool,
much less do lying lips fit a prince.

# Section: A bribe is a precious stone in the eyes of him who gives it;
# Proverbs 17:08
A bribe is a precious stone in the eyes of him who gives it;
wherever he turns,
he prospers.

# Section: He who covers an offense promotes love;
# Proverbs 17:09
He who covers an offense promotes love;
but he who repeats a matter separates best friends.

# Section: A rebuke enters deeper into one who has understanding
# Proverbs 17:10
A rebuke enters deeper into one who has understanding
than a hundred lashes into a fool.

# Section: An evil man seeks only rebellion;
# Proverbs 17:11
An evil man seeks only rebellion;
therefore a cruel messenger shall be sent against him.

# Section: Let a bear robbed of her cubs meet a man,
# Proverbs 17:12
Let a bear robbed of her cubs meet a man,
rather than a fool in his folly.

# Section: Whoever rewards evil for good,
# Proverbs 17:13
Whoever rewards evil for good,
evil shall not depart from his house.

# Section: The beginning of strife is like breaching a dam,
# Proverbs 17:14
The beginning of strife is like breaching a dam,
therefore stop contention before quarreling breaks out.

# Section: He who justifies the wicked,
# Proverbs 17:15
He who justifies the wicked,
and he who condemns the righteous,
both of them alike are an abomination to Yahweh.

# Section: Why is there money in the hand of a fool to buy wisdom,
# Proverbs 17:16
Why is there money in the hand of a fool to buy wisdom,
since he has no understanding?

# Section: A friend loves at all times;
# Proverbs 17:17
A friend loves at all times;
and a brother is born for adversity.

# Section: A man void of understanding strikes hands,
# Proverbs 17:18
A man void of understanding strikes hands,
and becomes collateral in the presence of his neighbor.

# Section: He who loves disobedience loves strife.
# Proverbs 17:19
He who loves disobedience loves strife.

One who builds a high gate seeks destruction.

# Section: One who has a perverse heart doesn’t find prosperity,
# Proverbs 17:20
One who has a perverse heart doesn’t find prosperity,
and one who has a deceitful tongue falls into trouble.

# Section: He who becomes the father of a fool grieves.
# Proverbs 17:21
He who becomes the father of a fool grieves.

The father of a fool has no joy.

# Section: A cheerful heart makes good medicine,
# Proverbs 17:22
A cheerful heart makes good medicine,
but a crushed spirit dries up the bones.

# Section: A wicked man receives a bribe in secret,
# Proverbs 17:23
A wicked man receives a bribe in secret,
to pervert the ways of justice.

# Section: Wisdom is before the face of one who has understanding,
# Proverbs 17:24
Wisdom is before the face of one who has understanding,
but the eyes of a fool wander to the ends of the earth.

# Section: A foolish son brings grief to his father,
# Proverbs 17:25
A foolish son brings grief to his father,
and bitterness to her who bore him.

# Section: Also to punish the righteous is not good,
# Proverbs 17:26
Also to punish the righteous is not good,
nor to flog officials for their integrity.

# Section: He who spares his words has knowledge.
# Proverbs 17:27
He who spares his words has knowledge.

He who is even tempered is a man of understanding.

# Section: Even a fool,
# Proverbs 17:28
Even a fool,
when he keeps silent,
is counted wise.

When he shuts his lips,
he is thought to be discerning.

# Section: A man who isolates himself pursues selfishness,
# Proverbs 18:01
A man who isolates himself pursues selfishness,
and defies all sound judgment.

# Section: A fool has no delight in understanding,
# Proverbs 18:02
A fool has no delight in understanding,
but only in revealing his own opinion.

# Section: When wickedness comes,
# Proverbs 18:03
When wickedness comes,
contempt also comes,
and with shame comes disgrace.

# Section: The words of a man's mouth are like deep waters.
# Proverbs 18:04
The words of a man's mouth are like deep waters.

The fountain of wisdom is like a flowing brook.

# Section: To be partial to the faces of the wicked is not good,
# Proverbs 18:05
To be partial to the faces of the wicked is not good,
nor to deprive the innocent of justice.

# Section: A fool's lips come into strife,
# Proverbs 18:06
A fool's lips come into strife,
and his mouth invites beatings.

# Section: A fool's mouth is his destruction,
# Proverbs 18:07
A fool's mouth is his destruction,
and his lips are a snare to his soul.

# Section: The words of a gossip are like dainty morsels:
# Proverbs 18:08
The words of a gossip are like dainty morsels:
they go down into a person's innermost parts.

# Proverbs 18:09
One who is slack in his work is brother to him who is a master of destruction.

# Section: Yahweh's name is a strong tower:
# Proverbs 18:10
Yahweh's name is a strong tower:
the righteous run to him,
and are safe.

# Section: The rich man's wealth is his strong city,
# Proverbs 18:11
The rich man's wealth is his strong city,
like an unscalable wall in his own imagination.

# Section: Before destruction the heart of man is proud,
# Proverbs 18:12
Before destruction the heart of man is proud,
but before honor is humility.

# Section: He who answers before he hears,
# Proverbs 18:13
He who answers before he hears,
that is folly and shame to him.

# Section: A man's spirit will sustain him in sickness,
# Proverbs 18:14
A man's spirit will sustain him in sickness,
but a crushed spirit,
who can bear?

# Section: The heart of the discerning gets knowledge.
# Proverbs 18:15
The heart of the discerning gets knowledge.

The ear of the wise seeks knowledge.

# Section: A man's gift makes room for him,
# Proverbs 18:16
A man's gift makes room for him,
and brings him before great men.

# Section: He who pleads his cause first seems right ---  until another comes and questions him.
# Proverbs 18:17
He who pleads his cause first seems right ---  until another comes and questions him.

# Section: The lot settles disputes,
# Proverbs 18:18
The lot settles disputes,
and keeps strong ones apart.

# Section: A brother offended is more difficult than a fortified city.
# Proverbs 18:19
A brother offended is more difficult than a fortified city.

Disputes are like the bars of a fortress.

# Section: A man's stomach is filled with the fruit of his mouth.
# Proverbs 18:20
A man's stomach is filled with the fruit of his mouth.

With the harvest of his lips he is satisfied.

# Section: Death and life are in the power of the tongue;
# Proverbs 18:21
Death and life are in the power of the tongue;
those who love it will eat its fruit.

# Section: Whoever finds a wife finds a good thing,
# Proverbs 18:22
Whoever finds a wife finds a good thing,
and obtains favor of Yahweh.

# Section: The poor plead for mercy,
# Proverbs 18:23
The poor plead for mercy,
but the rich answer harshly.

# Section: A man of many companions may be ruined,
# Proverbs 18:24
A man of many companions may be ruined,
but there is a friend who sticks closer than a brother.

# Section: Better is the poor who walks in his integrity than he who is perverse in his lips and is a fool.
# Proverbs 19:01
Better is the poor who walks in his integrity than he who is perverse in his lips and is a fool.

# Section: It isn’t good to have zeal without knowledge,
# Proverbs 19:02
It isn’t good to have zeal without knowledge,
nor being hasty with one's feet and missing the way.

# Section: The foolishness of man subverts his way;
# Proverbs 19:03
The foolishness of man subverts his way;
his heart rages against Yahweh.

# Section: Wealth adds many friends,
# Proverbs 19:04
Wealth adds many friends,
but the poor is separated from his friend.

# Section: A false witness shall not be unpunished.
# Proverbs 19:05
A false witness shall not be unpunished.

He who pours out lies shall not go free.

# Section: Many will entreat the favor of a ruler,
# Proverbs 19:06
Many will entreat the favor of a ruler,
and everyone is a friend to a man who gives gifts.

# Section: All the relatives of the poor shun him;
# Proverbs 19:07
All the relatives of the poor shun him;
how much more do his friends avoid him!

He pursues them with pleas,
but they are gone.

# Section: He who gets wisdom loves his own soul.
# Proverbs 19:08
He who gets wisdom loves his own soul.

He who keeps understanding shall find good.

# Section: A false witness shall not be unpunished.
# Proverbs 19:09
A false witness shall not be unpunished.

He who utters lies shall perish.

# Section: Delicate living is not appropriate for a fool,
# Proverbs 19:10
Delicate living is not appropriate for a fool,
much less for a servant to have rule over princes.

# Section: The discretion of a man makes him slow to anger.
# Proverbs 19:11
The discretion of a man makes him slow to anger.

It is his glory to overlook an offense.

# Section: The king's wrath is like the roaring of a lion,
# Proverbs 19:12
The king's wrath is like the roaring of a lion,
but his favor is like dew on the grass.

# Section: A foolish son is the calamity of his father.
# Proverbs 19:13
A foolish son is the calamity of his father.

A wife's quarrels are a continual dripping.

# Section: House and riches are an inheritance from fathers,
# Proverbs 19:14
House and riches are an inheritance from fathers,
but a prudent wife is from Yahweh.

# Section: Slothfulness casts into a deep sleep.
# Proverbs 19:15
Slothfulness casts into a deep sleep.

The idle soul shall suffer hunger.

# Section: He who keeps the commandment keeps his soul,
# Proverbs 19:16
He who keeps the commandment keeps his soul,
but he who is contemptuous in his ways shall die.

# Section: He who has pity on the poor lends to Yahweh;
# Proverbs 19:17
He who has pity on the poor lends to Yahweh;
he will reward him.

# Section: Discipline your son,
# Proverbs 19:18
Discipline your son,
for there is hope;
don't be a willing party to his death.

# Section: A hot-tempered man must pay the penalty,
# Proverbs 19:19
A hot-tempered man must pay the penalty,
for if you rescue him,
you must do it again.

# Section: Listen to counsel and receive instruction,
# Proverbs 19:20
Listen to counsel and receive instruction,
that you may be wise in your latter end.

# Section: There are many plans in a man's heart,
# Proverbs 19:21
There are many plans in a man's heart,
but Yahweh's counsel will prevail.

# Section: That which makes a man to be desired is his kindness.
# Proverbs 19:22
That which makes a man to be desired is his kindness.

A poor man is better than a liar.

# Section: The fear of Yahweh leads to life,
# Proverbs 19:23
The fear of Yahweh leads to life,
then contentment;
he rests and will not be touched by trouble.

# Section: The sluggard buries his hand in the dish;
# Proverbs 19:24
The sluggard buries his hand in the dish;
he will not so much as bring it to his mouth again.

# Section: Flog a scoffer,
# Proverbs 19:25
Flog a scoffer,
and the simple will learn prudence;
rebuke one who has understanding,
and he will gain knowledge.

# Proverbs 19:26
He who robs his father and drives away his mother is a son who causes shame and brings reproach.

# Section: If you stop listening to instruction,
# Proverbs 19:27
If you stop listening to instruction,
my son,
you will stray from the words of knowledge.

# Section: A corrupt witness mocks justice,
# Proverbs 19:28
A corrupt witness mocks justice,
and the mouth of the wicked gulps down iniquity.

# Section: Penalties are prepared for scoffers,
# Proverbs 19:29
Penalties are prepared for scoffers,
and beatings for the backs of fools.

# Section: Wine is a mocker and beer is a brawler.
# Proverbs 20:01
Wine is a mocker and beer is a brawler.

Whoever is led astray by them is not wise.

# Section: The terror of a king is like the roaring of a lion.
# Proverbs 20:02
The terror of a king is like the roaring of a lion.

He who provokes him to anger forfeits his own life.

# Section: It is an honor for a man to keep aloof from strife,
# Proverbs 20:03
It is an honor for a man to keep aloof from strife,
but every fool will be quarreling.

# Section: The sluggard will not plow by reason of the winter;
# Proverbs 20:04
The sluggard will not plow by reason of the winter;
therefore he shall beg in harvest,
and have nothing.

# Section: Counsel in the heart of man is like deep water,
# Proverbs 20:05
Counsel in the heart of man is like deep water,
but a man of understanding will draw it out.

# Section: Many men claim to be men of unfailing love,
# Proverbs 20:06
Many men claim to be men of unfailing love,
but who can find a faithful man?

# Section: A righteous man walks in integrity.
# Proverbs 20:07
A righteous man walks in integrity.

Blessed are his children after him.

# Section: A king who sits on the throne of judgment scatters away all evil with his eyes.
# Proverbs 20:08
A king who sits on the throne of judgment scatters away all evil with his eyes.

# Section: Who can say,
# Proverbs 20:09
Who can say,
``I have made my heart pure.

I am clean and without sin?''

# Section: Differing weights and differing measures,
# Proverbs 20:10
Differing weights and differing measures,
both of them alike are an abomination to Yahweh.

# Section: Even a child makes himself known by his doings,
# Proverbs 20:11
Even a child makes himself known by his doings,
whether his work is pure,
and whether it is right.

# Section: The hearing ear,
# Proverbs 20:12
The hearing ear,
and the seeing eye,
Yahweh has made even both of them.

# Section: Don't love sleep,
# Proverbs 20:13
Don't love sleep,
lest you come to poverty.

Open your eyes,
and you shall be satisfied with bread.

# Section: It's no good
# Proverbs 20:14
``It's no good,
it's no good,'' says the buyer;
but when he is gone his way,
then he boasts.

# Section: There is gold and abundance of rubies,
# Proverbs 20:15
There is gold and abundance of rubies,
but the lips of knowledge are a rare jewel.

# Section: Take the garment of one who puts up collateral for a stranger;
# Proverbs 20:16
Take the garment of one who puts up collateral for a stranger;
and hold him in pledge for a wayward woman.

# Section: Fraudulent food is sweet to a man,
# Proverbs 20:17
Fraudulent food is sweet to a man,
but afterwards his mouth is filled with gravel.

# Section: Plans are established by advice;
# Proverbs 20:18
Plans are established by advice;
by wise guidance you wage war!

# Section: He who goes about as a tale-bearer reveals secrets;
# Proverbs 20:19
He who goes about as a tale-bearer reveals secrets;
therefore don't keep company with him who opens wide his lips.

# Section: Whoever curses his father or his mother,
# Proverbs 20:20
Whoever curses his father or his mother,
his lamp shall be put out in blackness of darkness.

# Section: An inheritance quickly gained at the beginning won’t be blessed in the end.
# Proverbs 20:21
An inheritance quickly gained at the beginning won’t be blessed in the end.

# Section: Don't say,
# Proverbs 20:22
Don't say,
``I will pay back evil.''

Wait for Yahweh,
and he will save you.

# Section: Yahweh detests differing weights,
# Proverbs 20:23
Yahweh detests differing weights,
and dishonest scales are not pleasing.

# Section: A man's steps are from Yahweh;
# Proverbs 20:24
A man's steps are from Yahweh;
how then can man understand his way?

# Section: It is a snare to a man to make a rash dedication,
# Proverbs 20:25
It is a snare to a man to make a rash dedication,
then later to consider his vows.

# Section: A wise king winnows out the wicked,
# Proverbs 20:26
A wise king winnows out the wicked,
and drives the threshing wheel over them.

# Section: The spirit of man is Yahweh's lamp,
# Proverbs 20:27
The spirit of man is Yahweh's lamp,
searching all his innermost parts.

# Section: Love and faithfulness keep the king safe.
# Proverbs 20:28
Love and faithfulness keep the king safe.

His throne is sustained by love.

# Section: The glory of young men is their strength.
# Proverbs 20:29
The glory of young men is their strength.

The splendor of old men is their gray hair.

# Section: Wounding blows cleanse away evil,
# Proverbs 20:30
Wounding blows cleanse away evil,
and beatings purge the innermost parts.

# Section: The king's heart is in Yahweh's hand like the watercourses.
# Proverbs 21:01
The king's heart is in Yahweh's hand like the watercourses.

He turns it wherever he desires.

# Section: Every way of a man is right in his own eyes,
# Proverbs 21:02
Every way of a man is right in his own eyes,
but Yahweh weighs the hearts.

# Section: To do righteousness and justice is more acceptable to Yahweh than sacrifice.
# Proverbs 21:03
To do righteousness and justice is more acceptable to Yahweh than sacrifice.

# Section: A high look and a proud heart,
# Proverbs 21:04
A high look and a proud heart,
the lamp of the wicked,
is sin.

# Section: The plans of the diligent surely lead to profit;
# Proverbs 21:05
The plans of the diligent surely lead to profit;
and everyone who is hasty surely rushes to poverty.

# Section: Getting treasures by a lying tongue is a fleeting vapor for those who seek death.
# Proverbs 21:06
Getting treasures by a lying tongue is a fleeting vapor for those who seek death.

# Section: The violence of the wicked will drive them away,
# Proverbs 21:07
The violence of the wicked will drive them away,
because they refuse to do what is right.

# Section: The way of the guilty is devious,
# Proverbs 21:08
The way of the guilty is devious,
but the conduct of the innocent is upright.

# Section: It is better to dwell in the corner of the housetop than to share a house with a contentious woman.
# Proverbs 21:09
It is better to dwell in the corner of the housetop than to share a house with a contentious woman.

# Section: The soul of the wicked desires evil;
# Proverbs 21:10
The soul of the wicked desires evil;
his neighbor finds no mercy in his eyes.

# Section: When the mocker is punished,
# Proverbs 21:11
When the mocker is punished,
the simple gains wisdom.

When the wise is instructed,
he receives knowledge.

# Section: The Righteous One considers the house of the wicked,
# Proverbs 21:12
The Righteous One considers the house of the wicked,
and brings the wicked to ruin.

# Section: Whoever stops his ears at the cry of the poor,
# Proverbs 21:13
Whoever stops his ears at the cry of the poor,
he will also cry out,
but shall not be heard.

# Section: A gift in secret pacifies anger,
# Proverbs 21:14
A gift in secret pacifies anger,
and a bribe in the cloak,
strong wrath.

# Section: It is joy to the righteous to do justice;
# Proverbs 21:15
It is joy to the righteous to do justice;
but it is a destruction to the workers of iniquity.

# Section: The man who wanders out of the way of understanding shall rest in the assembly of the departed spirits.
# Proverbs 21:16
The man who wanders out of the way of understanding shall rest in the assembly of the departed spirits.

# Section: He who loves pleasure will be a poor man.
# Proverbs 21:17
He who loves pleasure will be a poor man.

He who loves wine and oil won’t be rich.

# Section: The wicked is a ransom for the righteous,
# Proverbs 21:18
The wicked is a ransom for the righteous,
the treacherous for the upright.

# Section: It is better to dwell in a desert land,
# Proverbs 21:19
It is better to dwell in a desert land,
than with a contentious and fretful woman.

# Section: There is precious treasure and oil in the dwelling of the wise,
# Proverbs 21:20
There is precious treasure and oil in the dwelling of the wise,
but a foolish man swallows it up.

# Section: He who follows after righteousness and kindness finds life,
# Proverbs 21:21
He who follows after righteousness and kindness finds life,
righteousness,
and honor.

# Section: A wise man scales the city of the mighty,
# Proverbs 21:22
A wise man scales the city of the mighty,
and brings down the strength of its confidence.

# Section: Whoever guards his mouth and his tongue keeps his soul from troubles.
# Proverbs 21:23
Whoever guards his mouth and his tongue keeps his soul from troubles.

# Section: The proud and arrogant man ---
# Proverbs 21:24
The proud and arrogant man ---
``
Scoffer'' is his name ---  he works in the arrogance of pride.

# Section: The desire of the sluggard kills him,
# Proverbs 21:25
The desire of the sluggard kills him,
for his hands refuse to labor.

# Section: There are those who covet greedily all day long;
# Proverbs 21:26
There are those who covet greedily all day long;
but the righteous give and don't withhold.

# Section: The sacrifice of the wicked is an abomination ---  how much more,
# Proverbs 21:27
The sacrifice of the wicked is an abomination ---  how much more,
when he brings it with a wicked mind!

# Section: A false witness will perish.
# Proverbs 21:28
A false witness will perish.

A man who listens speaks to eternity.

# Section: A wicked man hardens his face;
# Proverbs 21:29
A wicked man hardens his face;
but as for the upright,
he establishes his ways.

# Section: There is no wisdom nor understanding nor counsel against Yahweh.
# Proverbs 21:30
There is no wisdom nor understanding nor counsel against Yahweh.

# Section: The horse is prepared for the day of battle;
# Proverbs 21:31
The horse is prepared for the day of battle;
but victory is with Yahweh.

# Section: A good name is more desirable than great riches,
# Proverbs 22:01
A good name is more desirable than great riches,
and loving favor is better than silver and gold.

# Section: The rich and the poor have this in common:
# Proverbs 22:02
The rich and the poor have this in common:
Yahweh is the maker of them all.

# Section: A prudent man sees danger and hides himself;
# Proverbs 22:03
A prudent man sees danger and hides himself;
but the simple pass on,
and suffer for it.

# Section: The result of humility and the fear of Yahweh is wealth,
# Proverbs 22:04
The result of humility and the fear of Yahweh is wealth,
honor,
and life.

# Section: Thorns and snares are in the path of the wicked;
# Proverbs 22:05
Thorns and snares are in the path of the wicked;
whoever guards his soul stays from them.

# Section: Train up a child in the way he should go,
# Proverbs 22:06
Train up a child in the way he should go,
and when he is old he will not depart from it.

# Section: The rich rule over the poor.
# Proverbs 22:07
The rich rule over the poor.

The borrower is servant to the lender.

# Section: He who sows wickedness reaps trouble,
# Proverbs 22:08
He who sows wickedness reaps trouble,
and the rod of his fury will be destroyed.

# Section: He who has a generous eye will be blessed,
# Proverbs 22:09
He who has a generous eye will be blessed,
for he shares his food with the poor.

# Section: Drive out the mocker,
# Proverbs 22:10
Drive out the mocker,
and strife will go out;
yes,
quarrels and insults will stop.

# Section: He who loves purity of heart and speaks gracefully is the king's friend.
# Proverbs 22:11
He who loves purity of heart and speaks gracefully is the king's friend.

# Section: Yahweh's eyes watch over knowledge,
# Proverbs 22:12
Yahweh's eyes watch over knowledge,
but he frustrates the words of the unfaithful.

# Section: The sluggard says,
# Proverbs 22:13
The sluggard says,
``There is a lion outside!

I will be killed in the streets!''

# Section: The mouth of an adulteress is a deep pit.
# Proverbs 22:14
The mouth of an adulteress is a deep pit.

He who is under Yahweh's wrath will fall into it.

# Section: Folly is bound up in the heart of a child;
# Proverbs 22:15
Folly is bound up in the heart of a child;
the rod of discipline drives it far from him.

# Section: Whoever oppresses the poor for his own increase and whoever gives to the rich,
# Proverbs 22:16
Whoever oppresses the poor for his own increase and whoever gives to the rich,
both come to poverty.

# Section: Turn your ear,
# Proverbs 22:17
Turn your ear,
and listen to the words of the wise.

Apply your heart to my teaching.

# Section: For it is a pleasant thing if you keep them within you,
# Proverbs 22:18
For it is a pleasant thing if you keep them within you,
if all of them are ready on your lips.

# Section: I teach you today,
# Proverbs 22:19
I teach you today,
even you,
so that your trust may be in Yahweh.

# Section: Haven’t I written to you thirty excellent things of counsel and knowledge,
# Proverbs 22:20
Haven’t I written to you thirty excellent things of counsel and knowledge,

# Section: To teach you truth,
# Proverbs 22:21
To teach you truth,
reliable words,
to give sound answers to the ones who sent you?

# Section: Don't exploit the poor because he is poor;
# Proverbs 22:22
Don't exploit the poor because he is poor;
and don't crush the needy in court;

# Section: for Yahweh will plead their case,
# Proverbs 22:23
for Yahweh will plead their case,
and plunder the life of those who plunder them.

# Section: Don't befriend a hot-tempered man.
# Proverbs 22:24
Don't befriend a hot-tempered man.

Don't associate with one who harbors anger,

# Section: lest you learn his ways and ensnare your soul.
# Proverbs 22:25
lest you learn his ways and ensnare your soul.

# Section: Don't you be one of those who strike hands,
# Proverbs 22:26
Don't you be one of those who strike hands,
of those who are collateral for debts.

# Section: If you don't have means to pay,
# Proverbs 22:27
If you don't have means to pay,
why should he take away your bed from under you?

# Section: Don't move the ancient boundary stone which your fathers have set up.
# Proverbs 22:28
Don't move the ancient boundary stone which your fathers have set up.

# Section: Do you see a man skilled in his work?
# Proverbs 22:29
Do you see a man skilled in his work?

He will serve kings.

He won’t serve obscure men.

# Section: When you sit to eat with a ruler,
# Proverbs 23:01
When you sit to eat with a ruler,
consider diligently what is before you;

# Section: put a knife to your throat if you are a man given to appetite.
# Proverbs 23:02
put a knife to your throat if you are a man given to appetite.

# Section: Don't be desirous of his dainties,
# Proverbs 23:03
Don't be desirous of his dainties,
since they are deceitful food.

# Section: Don't weary yourself to be rich.
# Proverbs 23:04
Don't weary yourself to be rich.

In your wisdom,
show restraint.

# Section: Why do you set your eyes on that which is not?
# Proverbs 23:05
Why do you set your eyes on that which is not?

For it certainly sprouts wings like an eagle and flies in the sky.

# Section: Don't eat the food of him who has a stingy eye,
# Proverbs 23:06
Don't eat the food of him who has a stingy eye,
and don't crave his delicacies,

# Section: for as he thinks about the cost,
# Proverbs 23:07
for as he thinks about the cost,
so he is.

``Eat and drink!''

he says to you,
but his heart is not with you.

# Section: You will vomit up the morsel which you have eaten and waste your pleasant words.
# Proverbs 23:08
You will vomit up the morsel which you have eaten and waste your pleasant words.

# Section: Don't speak in the ears of a fool,
# Proverbs 23:09
Don't speak in the ears of a fool,
for he will despise the wisdom of your words.

# Section: Don't move the ancient boundary stone.
# Proverbs 23:10
Don't move the ancient boundary stone.

Don't encroach on the fields of the fatherless,

# Section: for their Defender is strong.
# Proverbs 23:11
for their Defender is strong.

He will plead their case against you.

# Section: Apply your heart to instruction,
# Proverbs 23:12
Apply your heart to instruction,
and your ears to the words of knowledge.

# Section: Don't withhold correction from a child.
# Proverbs 23:13
Don't withhold correction from a child.

If you punish him with the rod,
he will not die.

# Section: Punish him with the rod,
# Proverbs 23:14
Punish him with the rod,
and save his soul from Sheol.

# Section: My son,
# Proverbs 23:15
My son,
if your heart is wise,
then my heart will be glad,
even mine.

# Section: Yes,
# Proverbs 23:16
Yes,
my heart will rejoice when your lips speak what is right.

# Section: Don't let your heart envy sinners,
# Proverbs 23:17
Don't let your heart envy sinners,
but rather fear Yahweh all day long.

# Section: Indeed surely there is a future hope,
# Proverbs 23:18
Indeed surely there is a future hope,
and your hope will not be cut off.

# Section: Listen,
# Proverbs 23:19
Listen,
my son,
and be wise,
and keep your heart on the right path!

# Section: Don't be among ones drinking too much wine,
# Proverbs 23:20
Don't be among ones drinking too much wine,
or those who gorge themselves on meat;

# Section: for the drunkard and the glutton shall become poor;
# Proverbs 23:21
for the drunkard and the glutton shall become poor;
and drowsiness clothes them in rags.

# Section: Listen to your father who gave you life,
# Proverbs 23:22
Listen to your father who gave you life,
and don't despise your mother when she is old.

# Section: Buy the truth,
# Proverbs 23:23
Buy the truth,
and don't sell it.

Get wisdom,
discipline,
and understanding.

# Section: The father of the righteous has great joy.
# Proverbs 23:24
The father of the righteous has great joy.

Whoever fathers a wise child delights in him.

# Section: Let your father and your mother be glad!
# Proverbs 23:25
Let your father and your mother be glad!

Let her who bore you rejoice!

# Section: My son,
# Proverbs 23:26
My son,
give me your heart;
and let your eyes keep in my ways.

# Section: For a prostitute is a deep pit;
# Proverbs 23:27
For a prostitute is a deep pit;
and a wayward wife is a narrow well.

# Section: Yes,
# Proverbs 23:28
Yes,
she lies in wait like a robber,
and increases the unfaithful among men.

# Section: Who has woe?
# Proverbs 23:29
Who has woe?

Who has sorrow?

Who has strife?

Who has complaints?

Who has needless bruises?

Who has bloodshot eyes?

# Section: Those who stay long at the wine;
# Proverbs 23:30
Those who stay long at the wine;
those who go to seek out mixed wine.

# Section: Don't look at the wine when it is red,
# Proverbs 23:31
Don't look at the wine when it is red,
when it sparkles in the cup,
when it goes down smoothly.

# Section: In the end,
# Proverbs 23:32
In the end,
it bites like a snake,
and poisons like a viper.

# Section: Your eyes will see strange things,
# Proverbs 23:33
Your eyes will see strange things,
and your mind will imagine confusing things.

# Section: Yes,
# Proverbs 23:34
Yes,
you will be as he who lies down in the middle of the sea,
or as he who lies on top of the rigging:

# Section: They hit me,
# Proverbs 23:35
``They hit me,
and I was not hurt!

They beat me,
and I don't feel it!

When will I wake up?

I can do it again.

I will look for more.''

# Section: Don't be envious of evil men,
# Proverbs 24:01
Don't be envious of evil men,
neither desire to be with them;

# Section: for their hearts plot violence and their lips talk about mischief.
# Proverbs 24:02
for their hearts plot violence and their lips talk about mischief.

# Section: Through wisdom a house is built;
# Proverbs 24:03
Through wisdom a house is built;
by understanding it is established;
# Proverbs 24:04
by knowledge the rooms are filled with all rare and beautiful treasure.

# Section: A wise man has great power.
# Proverbs 24:05
A wise man has great power.

A knowledgeable man increases strength,
# Proverbs 24:06
for by wise guidance you wage your war,
and victory is in many advisors.

# Section: Wisdom is too high for a fool.
# Proverbs 24:07
Wisdom is too high for a fool.

He doesn’t open his mouth in the gate.

# Section: One who plots to do evil will be called a schemer.
# Proverbs 24:08
One who plots to do evil will be called a schemer.

# Section: The schemes of folly are sin.
# Proverbs 24:09
The schemes of folly are sin.

The mocker is detested by men.

# Section: If you falter in the time of trouble,
# Proverbs 24:10
If you falter in the time of trouble,
your strength is small.

# Section: Rescue those who are being led away to death!
# Proverbs 24:11
Rescue those who are being led away to death!

Indeed,
hold back those who are staggering to the slaughter!

# Section: If you say,
# Proverbs 24:12
If you say,
``Behold,
we didn’t know this,'' doesn’t he who weighs the hearts consider it?

He who keeps your soul,
doesn’t he know it?

Shall he not render to every man according to his work?

# Section: My son,
# Proverbs 24:13
My son,
eat honey,
for it is good,
the droppings of the honeycomb,
which are sweet to your taste;
# Proverbs 24:14
so you shall know wisdom to be to your soul.

If you have found it,
then there will be a reward:
Your hope will not be cut off.

# Section: Don't lay in wait,
# Proverbs 24:15
Don't lay in wait, wicked man,
against the habitation of the righteous.

Don't destroy his resting place;
# Proverbs 24:16
for a righteous man falls seven times and rises up again,
but the wicked are overthrown by calamity.

# Proverbs 24:17
Don't rejoice when your enemy falls.

Don't let your heart be glad when he is overthrown,
# Proverbs 24:18
lest Yahweh see it,
and it displease him,
and he turn away his wrath from him.

# Section: Don't fret yourself because of evildoers,
# Proverbs 24:19
Don't fret yourself because of evildoers,
neither be envious of the wicked;

# Proverbs 24:20
for there will be no reward to the evil man.

The lamp of the wicked will be snuffed out.

# Section: My son,
# Proverbs 24:21
My son,
fear Yahweh and the king.

Don't join those who are rebellious,

# Proverbs 24:22
for their calamity will rise suddenly.

Who knows what destruction may come from them both?

# Section: These also are sayings of the wise:
# Proverbs 24:23
These also are sayings of the wise:
To show partiality in judgment is not good.

# Section: He who says to the wicked,
# Proverbs 24:24
He who says to the wicked,
``You are righteous,'' peoples will curse him,
and nations will abhor him ---

# Proverbs 24:25
but it will go well with those who convict the guilty,
and a rich blessing will come on them.

# Section: An honest answer is like a kiss on the lips.
# Proverbs 24:26
An honest answer is like a kiss on the lips.

# Section: Prepare your work outside,
# Proverbs 24:27
Prepare your work outside,
and get your fields ready.

Afterwards,
build your house.

# Section: Don't be a witness against your neighbor without cause.
# Proverbs 24:28
Don't be a witness against your neighbor without cause.

Don't deceive with your lips.

# Section: Don't say,
# Proverbs 24:29
Don't say,
``I will do to him as he has done to me;
I will repay the man according to his work.''

# Section: I went by the field of the sluggard,
# Proverbs 24:30
I went by the field of the sluggard,
by the vineyard of the man void of understanding.

# Proverbs 24:31
Behold,
it was all grown over with thorns.

Its surface was covered with nettles,
and its stone wall was broken down.

# Proverbs 24:32
Then I saw,
and considered well.

I saw,
and received instruction:
  # Proverbs 24:33
  a little sleep,
  a little slumber,
  a little folding of the hands to sleep,
  # Proverbs 24:34
  so your poverty will come as a robber and your want as an armed man.

# Section: These also are proverbs of Solomon,
# Proverbs 25:01
These also are proverbs of Solomon,
which the men of Hezekiah king of Judah copied out.

# Section: It is the glory of God to conceal a thing,
# Proverbs 25:02
It is the glory of God to conceal a thing,
but the glory of kings is to search out a matter.

# Section: As the heavens for height,
# Proverbs 25:03
As the heavens for height,
and the earth for depth,
so the hearts of kings are unsearchable.

# Section: Take away the dross from the silver,
# Proverbs 25:04
Take away the dross from the silver,
and material comes out for the refiner.

# Section: Take away the wicked from the king's presence,
# Proverbs 25:05
Take away the wicked from the king's presence,
and his throne will be established in righteousness.

# Section: Don't exalt yourself in the presence of the king,
# Proverbs 25:06
Don't exalt yourself in the presence of the king,
or claim a place among great men;
# Proverbs 25:07
for it is better that it be said to you,
``Come up here,'' than that you should be put lower in the presence of the prince,
whom your eyes have seen.

# Section: Don't be hasty in bringing charges to court.
# Proverbs 25:08
Don't be hasty in bringing charges to court.

What will you do in the end when your neighbor shames you?

# Section: Debate your case with your neighbor,
# Proverbs 25:09
Debate your case with your neighbor,
and don't betray the confidence of another,
# Proverbs 25:10
lest one who hears it put you to shame,
and your bad reputation never depart.

# Proverbs 25:11
A word fitly spoken is like apples of gold in settings of silver.

# Section: As an earring of gold,
# Proverbs 25:12
As an earring of gold,
and an ornament of fine gold,
so is a wise reprover to an obedient ear.

# Section: As the cold of snow in the time of harvest,
# Proverbs 25:13
As the cold of snow in the time of harvest,
so is a faithful messenger to those who send him;
for he refreshes the soul of his masters.

# Section: As clouds and wind without rain,
# Proverbs 25:14
As clouds and wind without rain,
so is he who boasts of gifts deceptively.

# Section: By patience a ruler is persuaded.
# Proverbs 25:15
By patience a ruler is persuaded.

A soft tongue breaks the bone.

# Section: Have you found honey?
# Proverbs 25:16
Have you found honey?

Eat as much as is sufficient for you,
lest you eat too much,
and vomit it.

# Section: Let your foot be seldom in your neighbor's house,
# Proverbs 25:17
Let your foot be seldom in your neighbor's house,
lest he be weary of you,
and hate you.

# Section: A man who gives false testimony against his neighbor is like a club,
# Proverbs 25:18
A man who gives false testimony against his neighbor is like a club,
a sword,
or a sharp arrow.

# Section: Confidence in someone unfaithful in time of trouble is like a bad tooth or a lame foot.
# Proverbs 25:19
Confidence in someone unfaithful in time of trouble is like a bad tooth or a lame foot.

# Section: As one who takes away a garment in cold weather,
# Proverbs 25:20
As one who takes away a garment in cold weather,
or vinegar on soda,
so is one who sings songs to a heavy heart.

# Section: If your enemy is hungry,
# Proverbs 25:21
If your enemy is hungry,
give him food to eat.

If he is thirsty,
give him water to drink;

# Proverbs 25:22
for you will heap coals of fire on his head,
and Yahweh will reward you.

# Section: The north wind produces rain;
# Proverbs 25:23
The north wind produces rain;
so a backbiting tongue brings an angry face.

# Section: It is better to dwell in the corner of the housetop than to share a house with a contentious woman.
# Proverbs 25:24
It is better to dwell in the corner of the housetop than to share a house with a contentious woman.

# Section: Like cold water to a thirsty soul,
# Proverbs 25:25
Like cold water to a thirsty soul,
so is good news from a far country.

# Section: Like a muddied spring and a polluted well,
# Proverbs 25:26
Like a muddied spring and a polluted well,
so is a righteous man who gives way before the wicked.

# Section: It is not good to eat much honey,
# Proverbs 25:27
It is not good to eat much honey,
nor is it honorable to seek one's own honor.

# Section: Like a city that is broken down and without walls is a man whose spirit is without restraint.
# Proverbs 25:28
Like a city that is broken down and without walls is a man whose spirit is without restraint.

# Section: Like snow in summer,
# Proverbs 26:01
Like snow in summer,
and as rain in harvest,
so honor is not fitting for a fool.

# Section: Like a fluttering sparrow,
# Proverbs 26:02
Like a fluttering sparrow,
like a darting swallow,
so the undeserved curse doesn’t come to rest.

# Section: A whip is for the horse,
# Proverbs 26:03
A whip is for the horse,
a bridle for the donkey,
and a rod for the back of fools!

# Section: Don't answer a fool according to his folly,
# Proverbs 26:04
Don't answer a fool according to his folly,
lest you also be like him.

# Proverbs 26:05
Answer a fool according to his folly,
lest he be wise in his own eyes.

# Section: One who sends a message by the hand of a fool is cutting off feet and drinking violence.
# Proverbs 26:06
One who sends a message by the hand of a fool is cutting off feet and drinking violence.

# Section: Like the legs of the lame that hang loose,
# Proverbs 26:07
Like the legs of the lame that hang loose,
so is a parable in the mouth of fools.

# Section: As one who binds a stone in a sling,
# Proverbs 26:08
As one who binds a stone in a sling,
so is he who gives honor to a fool.

# Section: Like a thorn bush that goes into the hand of a drunkard,
# Proverbs 26:09
Like a thorn bush that goes into the hand of a drunkard,
so is a parable in the mouth of fools.

# Section: As an archer who wounds all,
# Proverbs 26:10
As an archer who wounds all,
so is he who hires a fool or he who hires those who pass by.

# Section: As a dog that returns to his vomit,
# Proverbs 26:11
As a dog that returns to his vomit,
so is a fool who repeats his folly.

# Section: Do you see a man wise in his own eyes?
# Proverbs 26:12
Do you see a man wise in his own eyes?

There is more hope for a fool than for him.

# Section: The sluggard says,
# Proverbs 26:13
The sluggard says,
``There is a lion in the road!

A fierce lion roams the streets!''

# Section: As the door turns on its hinges,
# Proverbs 26:14
As the door turns on its hinges,
so does the sluggard on his bed.

# Section: The sluggard buries his hand in the dish.
# Proverbs 26:15
The sluggard buries his hand in the dish.

He is too lazy to bring it back to his mouth.

# Section: The sluggard is wiser in his own eyes than seven men who answer with discretion.
# Proverbs 26:16
The sluggard is wiser in his own eyes than seven men who answer with discretion.

# Section: Like one who grabs a dog's ears is one who passes by and meddles in a quarrel not his own.
# Proverbs 26:17
Like one who grabs a dog's ears is one who passes by and meddles in a quarrel not his own.

# Section: Like a madman who shoots torches,
# Proverbs 26:18
Like a madman who shoots torches,
arrows,
and death,

# Section: is the man who deceives his neighbor and says,
# Proverbs 26:19
is the man who deceives his neighbor and says,
``Am I not joking?''

# Section: For lack of wood a fire goes out.
# Proverbs 26:20
For lack of wood a fire goes out.

Without gossip,
a quarrel dies down.

# Section: As coals are to hot embers,
# Proverbs 26:21
As coals are to hot embers,
and wood to fire,
so is a contentious man to kindling strife.

# Section: The words of a whisperer are as dainty morsels,
# Proverbs 26:22
The words of a whisperer are as dainty morsels,
they go down into the innermost parts.

# Section: Like silver dross on an earthen vessel are the lips of a fervent one with an evil heart.
# Proverbs 26:23
Like silver dross on an earthen vessel are the lips of a fervent one with an evil heart.

# Section: A malicious man disguises himself with his lips,
# Proverbs 26:24
A malicious man disguises himself with his lips,
but he harbors evil in his heart.

# Section: When his speech is charming,
# Proverbs 26:25
When his speech is charming,
don't believe him,
for there are seven abominations in his heart.

# Section: His malice may be concealed by deception,
# Proverbs 26:26
His malice may be concealed by deception,
but his wickedness will be exposed in the assembly.

# Section: Whoever digs a pit shall fall into it.
# Proverbs 26:27
Whoever digs a pit shall fall into it.

Whoever rolls a stone,
it will come back on him.

# Section: A lying tongue hates those it hurts;
# Proverbs 26:28
A lying tongue hates those it hurts;
and a flattering mouth works ruin.

# Section: Don't boast about tomorrow;
# Proverbs 27:01
Don't boast about tomorrow;
for you don't know what a day may bring.

# Section: Let another man praise you,
# Proverbs 27:02
Let another man praise you,
and not your own mouth;
a stranger,
and not your own lips.

# Section: A stone is heavy,
# Proverbs 27:03
A stone is heavy,
and sand is a burden;
but a fool's provocation is heavier than both.

# Section: Wrath is cruel,
# Proverbs 27:04
Wrath is cruel,
and anger is overwhelming;
but who is able to stand before jealousy?

# Section: Better is open rebuke than hidden love.
# Proverbs 27:05
Better is open rebuke than hidden love.

# Section: The wounds of a friend are faithful,
# Proverbs 27:06
The wounds of a friend are faithful,
although the kisses of an enemy are profuse.

# Section: A full soul loathes a honeycomb;
# Proverbs 27:07
A full soul loathes a honeycomb;
but to a hungry soul,
every bitter thing is sweet.

# Section: As a bird that wanders from her nest,
# Proverbs 27:08
As a bird that wanders from her nest,
so is a man who wanders from his home.

# Section: Perfume and incense bring joy to the heart;
# Proverbs 27:09
Perfume and incense bring joy to the heart;
so does earnest counsel from a man's friend.

# Section: Don't forsake your friend and your father's friend.
# Proverbs 27:10
Don't forsake your friend and your father's friend.

Don't go to your brother's house in the day of your disaster.

A neighbor who is near is better than a distant brother.

# Section: Be wise, my son,
# Proverbs 27:11
Be wise, my son,
and bring joy to my heart,
then I can answer my tormentor.

# Section: A prudent man sees danger and takes refuge;
# Proverbs 27:12
A prudent man sees danger and takes refuge;
but the simple pass on,
and suffer for it.

# Section: Take his garment when he puts up collateral for a stranger.
# Proverbs 27:13
Take his garment when he puts up collateral for a stranger.

Hold it for a wayward woman!

# Section: He who blesses his neighbor with a loud voice early in the morning,
# Proverbs 27:14
He who blesses his neighbor with a loud voice early in the morning,
it will be taken as a curse by him.

# Section: A continual dropping on a rainy day and a contentious wife are alike:
# Proverbs 27:15
A continual dropping on a rainy day and a contentious wife are alike:

# Proverbs 27:16
restraining her is like restraining the wind,
or like grasping oil in his right hand.

# Section: Iron sharpens iron;
# Proverbs 27:17
Iron sharpens iron;
so a man sharpens his friend's countenance.

# Section: Whoever tends the fig tree shall eat its fruit.
# Proverbs 27:18
Whoever tends the fig tree shall eat its fruit.

He who looks after his master shall be honored.

# Section: Like water reflects a face,
# Proverbs 27:19
Like water reflects a face,
so a man's heart reflects the man.

# Section: Sheol and Abaddon are never satisfied;
# Proverbs 27:20
Sheol and Abaddon are never satisfied;
and a man's eyes are never satisfied.

# Section: The crucible is for silver,
# Proverbs 27:21
The crucible is for silver,
and the furnace for gold;
but man is refined by his praise.

# Section: Though you grind a fool in a mortar with a pestle along with grain,
# Proverbs 27:22
Though you grind a fool in a mortar with a pestle along with grain,
yet his foolishness will not be removed from him.

# Section: Know well the state of your flocks,
# Proverbs 27:23
Know well the state of your flocks,
and pay attention to your herds,

# Proverbs 27:24
for riches are not forever,
nor does the crown endure to all generations.

# Section: The hay is removed,
# Proverbs 27:25
The hay is removed,
and the new growth appears,
the grasses of the hills are gathered in.

# Section: The lambs are for your clothing,
# Proverbs 27:26
The lambs are for your clothing,
and the goats are the price of a field.

# Section: There will be plenty of goats’ milk for your food,
# Proverbs 27:27
There will be plenty of goats’ milk for your food,
for your family's food,
and for the nourishment of your servant girls.

# Section: The wicked flee when no one pursues;
# Proverbs 28:01
The wicked flee when no one pursues;
but the righteous are as bold as a lion.

# Section: In rebellion,
# Proverbs 28:02
In rebellion,
a land has many rulers,
but order is maintained by a man of understanding and knowledge.

# Section: A needy man who oppresses the poor is like a driving rain which leaves no crops.
# Proverbs 28:03
A needy man who oppresses the poor is like a driving rain which leaves no crops.

# Section: Those who forsake the law praise the wicked;
# Proverbs 28:04
Those who forsake the law praise the wicked;
but those who keep the law contend with them.

# Section: Evil men don't understand justice;
# Proverbs 28:05
Evil men don't understand justice;
but those who seek Yahweh understand it fully.

# Section: Better is the poor who walks in his integrity than he who is perverse in his ways,
# Proverbs 28:06
Better is the poor who walks in his integrity than he who is perverse in his ways,
and he is rich.

# Section: Whoever keeps the law is a wise son;
# Proverbs 28:07
Whoever keeps the law is a wise son;
but he who is a companion of gluttons shames his father.

# Section: He who increases his wealth by excessive interest gathers it for one who has pity on the poor.
# Proverbs 28:08
He who increases his wealth by excessive interest gathers it for one who has pity on the poor.

# Section: He who turns away his ear from hearing the law,
# Proverbs 28:09
He who turns away his ear from hearing the law,
even his prayer is an abomination.

# Section: Whoever causes the upright to go astray in an evil way,
# Proverbs 28:10
Whoever causes the upright to go astray in an evil way,
he will fall into his own trap;
but the blameless will inherit good.

# Section: The rich man is wise in his own eyes;
# Proverbs 28:11
The rich man is wise in his own eyes;
but the poor who has understanding sees through him.

# Section: When the righteous triumph,
# Proverbs 28:12
When the righteous triumph,
there is great glory;
but when the wicked rise,
men hide themselves.

# Section: He who conceals his sins doesn’t prosper,
# Proverbs 28:13
He who conceals his sins doesn’t prosper,
but whoever confesses and renounces them finds mercy.

# Section: Blessed is the man who always fears
# Proverbs 28:14
Blessed is the man who always fears;
but one who hardens his heart falls into trouble.

# Section: As a roaring lion or a charging bear
# Proverbs 28:15
As a roaring lion or a charging bear,
so is a wicked ruler over helpless people.

# Section: A tyrannical ruler lacks judgment.
# Proverbs 28:16
A tyrannical ruler lacks judgment.
One who hates ill-gotten gain will have long days.

# Section: A man who is tormented by blood guilt
# Proverbs 28:17
A man who is tormented by blood guilt will be a fugitive until death.
No one will support him.

# Section: Whoever walks blamelessly
# Proverbs 28:18
Whoever walks blamelessly is kept safe;
but one with perverse ways will fall suddenly.

# Section: One who works his land
# Proverbs 28:19
One who works his land will have an abundance of food;
but one who chases fantasies will have his fill of poverty.

# Section: A faithful man is rich with blessings
# Proverbs 28:20
A faithful man is rich with blessings;
but one who is eager to be rich will not go unpunished.

# Section: To show partiality is not good
# Proverbs 28:21
To show partiality is not good,
yet a man will do wrong for a piece of bread.

# Section: A stingy man
# Proverbs 28:22
A stingy man hurries after riches,
and doesn’t know that poverty waits for him.

# Section: One who rebukes a man
# Proverbs 28:23
One who rebukes a man will afterward find more favor
than one who flatters with the tongue.

# Section: Whoever robs his father or his mother
# Proverbs 28:24
Whoever robs his father or his mother and says,
{
  It's not wrong,
}

is a partner with a destroyer.

# Section: One who is greedy
# Proverbs 28:25
One who is greedy stirs up strife;
but one who trusts in Yahweh will prosper.

# Section: One who trusts in himself
# Proverbs 28:26
One who trusts in himself is a fool;
but one who walks in wisdom is kept safe.

# Section: One who gives to the poor
# Proverbs 28:27
One who gives to the poor has no lack;
but one who closes his eyes will have many curses.

# Section: When the wicked rise
# Proverbs 28:28
When the wicked rise,
  men hide themselves;
but when they perish,
  the righteous thrive.

# Section: He who is often rebuked and stiffens his neck
# Proverbs 29:01
He who is often rebuked and stiffens his neck will be destroyed suddenly,
with no remedy.

# Section: When the righteous thrive
# Proverbs 29:02
When the righteous thrive,
  the people rejoice;
but when the wicked rule,
  the people groan.

# Section: Whoever loves wisdom brings joy to his father
# Proverbs 29:03
Whoever loves wisdom brings joy to his father;
but a companion of prostitutes squanders his wealth.

# Section: The king by justice makes the land stable,
# Proverbs 29:04
The king by justice makes the land stable,
but he who takes bribes tears it down.

# Section: A man who flatters his neighbor
# Proverbs 29:05
A man who flatters his neighbor spreads a net for his feet.

# Section: An evil man is snared by his sin
# Proverbs 29:06
An evil man is snared by his sin,
but the righteous can sing and be glad.

# Section: The righteous care about justice for the poor.
# Proverbs 29:07
The righteous care about justice for the poor.
The wicked aren’t concerned about knowledge.

# Section: Mockers stir up a city
# Proverbs 29:08
Mockers stir up a city,
but wise men turn away anger.

# Section: If a wise man goes to court with a foolish man
# Proverbs 29:09
If a wise man goes to court with a foolish man,
the fool rages or scoffs,
and there is no peace.

# Section: The bloodthirsty hate a man of integrity
# Proverbs 29:10
The bloodthirsty hate a man of integrity;
and they seek the life of the upright.

# Section: A fool vents all of his anger
# Proverbs 29:11
A fool vents all of his anger,
but a wise man brings himself under control.

# Section: If a ruler listens to lies
# Proverbs 29:12
If a ruler listens to lies,
all of his officials are wicked.

# Section: The poor man and the oppressor have this in common
# Proverbs 29:13
The poor man and the oppressor have this in common:
Yahweh gives sight to the eyes of both.

# Section: The king who fairly judges the poor
# Proverbs 29:14
The king who fairly judges the poor,
his throne shall be established forever.

# Section: The rod of correction gives wisdom
# Proverbs 29:15
The rod of correction gives wisdom,
but a child left to himself causes shame to his mother.

# Section: When the wicked increase
# Proverbs 29:16
When the wicked increase, sin increases;
but the righteous will see their downfall.

# Section: Correct your son
# Proverbs 29:17
Correct your son, and he will give you peace;
yes, he will bring delight to your soul.

# Section: Where there is no revelation
# Proverbs 29:18
Where there is no revelation,
the people cast off restraint;
but one who keeps the law is blessed.

# Section: A servant can’t be corrected by words.
# Proverbs 29:19
A servant can’t be corrected by words.
Though he understands, yet he will not respond.

# Section: Do you see a man who is hasty in his words?
# Proverbs 29:20
Do you see a man who is hasty in his words?
There is more hope for a fool than for him.

# Section: He who pampers his servant from youth
# Proverbs 29:21
He who pampers his servant from youth
will have him become a son in the end.

# Section: An angry man stirs up strife
# Proverbs 29:22
An angry man stirs up strife,
and a wrathful man abounds in sin.

# Section: A man's pride brings him low
# Proverbs 29:23
A man's pride brings him low,
but one of lowly spirit gains honor.

# Section: Whoever is an accomplice of a thief
# Proverbs 29:24
Whoever is an accomplice of a thief is an enemy of his own soul.
He takes an oath, but dares not testify.

# Proverbs 29:25
The fear of man proves to be a snare,
but whoever puts his trust in Yahweh is kept safe.

# Section: Many seek the ruler's favor
# Proverbs 29:26
Many seek the ruler's favor,
but a man's justice comes from Yahweh.

# Section: A dishonest man detests the righteous
# Proverbs 29:27
A dishonest man detests the righteous,
and the upright in their ways detest the wicked.

# Section: The words of Agur
# Proverbs 30:01
The words of Agur the son of Jakeh,
the revelation:
the man says to Ithiel,
to Ithiel and Ucal:

{
  # Proverbs 30:02
  Surely I am the most ignorant man,
  and don't have a man's understanding.

  # Proverbs 30:03
  I have not learned wisdom,
  neither do I have the knowledge of the Holy One.

  # Proverbs 30:04
  Who has ascended up into heaven, and descended?

  Who has gathered the wind in his fists?

  Who has bound the waters in his garment?

  Who has established all the ends of the earth?

  What is his name, and what is his son's name,
  if you know?
}

# Section:   Every word of God is flawless.
# Proverbs 30:05
Every word of God is flawless.

He is a shield to those who take refuge in him.

# Proverbs 30:06
Don't you add to his words,
lest he reprove you,
and you be found a liar.

# Section:   Two things I have asked of you.
# Proverbs 30:07
Two things I have asked of you.

Don't deny me before I die.

# Proverbs 30:08
Remove far from me falsehood and lies.

Give me neither poverty nor riches.

Feed me with the food that is needful for me,
# Proverbs 30:09
lest I be full,
deny you,
and say,
{
  Who is Yahweh?
}

or lest I be poor,
and steal,
and so dishonor the name of my God.

# Section:   Don't slander a servant to his master
# Proverbs 30:10
Don't slander a servant to his master,
lest he curse you,
and you be held guilty.

# Proverbs 30:11
There is a generation that curses their father,
and doesn’t bless their mother.

# Proverbs 30:12
There is a generation that is pure in their own eyes,
yet are not washed from their filthiness.

# Proverbs 30:13
There is a generation,
oh how lofty are their eyes!

Their eyelids are lifted up.

# Proverbs 30:14
There is a generation whose teeth are like swords,
and their jaws like knives,
to devour the poor from the earth,
and the needy from among men.

# Section:   The leech has two daughters
# Proverbs 30:15
The leech has two daughters:
{
  Give, give.
}

# Section:   There are three things that are never satisfied
There are three things that are never satisfied;
four that don't say,
{
  Enough!
}

# Proverbs 30:16
Sheol,
the barren womb,
the earth that is not satisfied with water,
and the fire that doesn’t say,
{
  Enough!
}

# Proverbs 30:17
The eye that mocks at his father,
and scorns obedience to his mother,
the ravens of the valley shall pick it out,
the young eagles shall eat it.

# Section:   There are three things which are too amazing for me
# Proverbs 30:18
There are three things which are too amazing for me,
four which I don't understand:

# Proverbs 30:19
The way of an eagle in the air,
the way of a serpent on a rock,
the way of a ship in the middle of the sea,
and the way of a man with a maiden.

# Section: So is the way of an adulterous woman
# Proverbs 30:20
So is the way of an adulterous woman:
She eats and wipes her mouth,
and says,
{
  I have done nothing wrong.
}

# Section:   For three things the earth trembles,
# Proverbs 30:21
For three things the earth trembles,
and under four,
it can’t bear up:

# Proverbs 30:22
For a servant when he is king,
a fool when he is filled with food,
# Proverbs 30:23
for an unloved woman when she is married,
and a servant who is heir to her mistress.

# Section:   There are four things which are little on the earth
# Proverbs 30:24
{
  There are four things which are little on the earth,
  but they are exceedingly wise:

  # Proverbs 30:25
  The ants are not a strong people,
  yet they provide their food in the summer.

  # Proverbs 30:26
  The hyraxes are but a feeble folk,
  yet make they their houses in the rocks.

  # Proverbs 30:27
  The locusts have no king,
  yet they advance in ranks.

  # Proverbs 30:28
  You can catch a lizard with your hands,
  yet it is in kings’ palaces.
}

# Proverbs 30:29
There are three things which are stately in their march,
four which are stately in going:
# Proverbs 30:30
The lion,
which is mightiest among animals,
and doesn’t turn away for any;
# Proverbs 30:31
the greyhound;
the male goat;
and the king against whom there is no rising up.

# Section:   If you have done foolishly in lifting up yourself
# Proverbs 30:32
If you have done foolishly in lifting up yourself,
or if you have thought evil,
put your hand over your mouth.

# Proverbs 30:33
For as the churning of milk produces butter,
and the wringing of the nose produces blood,
so the forcing of wrath produces strife.

# Section: The words of King Lemuel
# Proverbs 31:01
The words of King Lemuel ---
the revelation which his mother taught him:
# Proverbs 31:02
{
  Oh, my son!

  Oh, son of my womb!

  Oh, son of my vows!

  # Proverbs 31:03
  Don't give your strength to women,
  nor your ways to that which destroys kings.

  # Proverbs 31:04
  It is not for kings,
  Lemuel,
  it is not for kings to drink wine,
  nor for princes to say,
  {
    Where is strong drink?
  }

  # Proverbs 31:05
  lest they drink,
  and forget the law,
  and pervert the justice due to anyone who is afflicted.

  # Proverbs 31:06
  Give strong drink to him who is ready to perish,
  and wine to the bitter in soul.

  # Proverbs 31:07
  Let him drink,
  and forget his poverty,
  and remember his misery no more.

  # Proverbs 31:08
  Open your mouth for the mute,
  in the cause of all who are left desolate.

  # Proverbs 31:09
  Open your mouth,
  judge righteously,
  and serve justice to the poor and needy.
}

# Section: Who can find a worthy woman?
# Proverbs 31:10
Who can find a worthy woman?

For her value is far above rubies.

# Proverbs 31:11
The heart of her husband trusts in her.

He shall have no lack of gain.

# Proverbs 31:12
She does him good, and not harm,
all the days of her life.

# Proverbs 31:13
She seeks wool and flax,
and works eagerly with her hands.

# Proverbs 31:14
She is like the merchant ships.

She brings her bread from afar.

# Proverbs 31:15
She rises also while it is yet night,
gives food to her household,
and portions for her servant girls.

# Proverbs 31:16
She considers a field,
  and buys it.
With the fruit of her hands,
  she plants a vineyard.

# Proverbs 31:17
She arms her waist with strength,
and makes her arms strong.

# Proverbs 31:18
She perceives that her merchandise is profitable.

Her lamp doesn’t go out by night.

# Proverbs 31:19
She lays her hands to the distaff,
and her hands hold the spindle.

# Proverbs 31:20
She opens her arms to the poor;
yes, she extends her hands to the needy.

# Proverbs 31:21
She is not afraid of the snow for her household,
for all her household are clothed with scarlet.

# Proverbs 31:22
She makes for herself carpets of tapestry.

Her clothing is fine linen and purple.

# Section: Her husband is respected in the gates
# Proverbs 31:23
Her husband is respected in the gates,
when he sits among the elders of the land.

# Proverbs 31:24
She makes linen garments and sells them,
and delivers sashes to the merchant.

# Proverbs 31:25
Strength and dignity are her clothing.

She laughs at the time to come.

# Proverbs 31:26
She opens her mouth with wisdom.

Kind instruction is on her tongue.

# Proverbs 31:27
She looks well to the ways of her household,
and doesn’t eat the bread of idleness.

# Proverbs 31:28
Her children rise up and call her blessed.

Her husband also praises her:
# Proverbs 31:29
{
  Many women do noble things,
  but you excel them all.
}

# Proverbs 31:30
Charm is deceitful,
and beauty is vain;
but a woman who fears Yahweh,
she shall be praised.

# Proverbs 31:31
Give her of the fruit of her hands!

Let her works praise her in the gates!

